Achievements.DESCRIPTION[MyFirstCity]: Build city with residential, commercial and industrial zones, water, and electricity.
Achievements.DESCRIPTION[TheInspector]: Have a look at each individual info view panel.
Achievements.DESCRIPTION[HappytobeofServ: Create a city district and assign a city service to that district.
Achievements.DESCRIPTION[RoyalFlush]: Reach enough milestones to unlock all city services in a single city.
Achievements.DESCRIPTION[KeyToTheCity]: Unlock each building available in the base game.
Achievements.DESCRIPTION[GoAnywhere]: Have 20 active transport lines. These can be passenger or cargo lines or any mix of the two.
Achievements.DESCRIPTION[MakingAMark]: Build 5 signature buildings in a single city.
Achievements.DESCRIPTION[EverythingTheLi: Unlock 150 map tiles in a single city.
Achievements.DESCRIPTION[ExecutiveDecisi: Assign a policy to a city district.
Achievements.DESCRIPTION[AllSmiles]: Have at least 1000 citizens and an average happiness rating of 75%.
Achievements.DESCRIPTION[YouLittleStalke: Follow a citizen's lifepath from childhood to old age.
Achievements.DESCRIPTION[TheGoodStuff]: Listen to two different radio stations around the clock each.
Achievements.DESCRIPTION[IMadeThis]: Use the editor to make an asset of any other type than a map.
Achievements.DESCRIPTION[Cartography]: Use the editor to make a map.
Achievements.DESCRIPTION[TheExplorer]: Unlock 50 map tiles in a single city.
Achievements.DESCRIPTION[TheArchitect]: Build 10 signature buildings in a single city.
Achievements.DESCRIPTION[FourSeasons]: Experience all four seasons by building a city in a climate with a snowy winter.
Achievements.DESCRIPTION[Spiderwebbing]: Have 50 active transport lines. These can be passenger or cargo lines or any mix of the two.
Achievements.DESCRIPTION[ThisIsNotMyHapp: Have at least 1000 citizens and an average happiness rating of 25%.
Achievements.DESCRIPTION[SimplyIrresisti: Have at least 1000 citizens and a city attractiveness rating of 90.
Achievements.DESCRIPTION[Snapshot]: Use the photo mode to take a screenshot.
Achievements.DESCRIPTION[TheDeepEnd]: Have a total loan of at least 200,000 in a single city.
Achievements.DESCRIPTION[ColossalGardene: Plant 100 trees or bushes with the landscaping tool in a single city.
Achievements.DESCRIPTION[StrengthThrough: Have buildings from all four zone types in a single city.
Achievements.DESCRIPTION[OneofEverything: Build all unique city service buildings in a single city.
Achievements.DESCRIPTION[ALittleBitofTLC: Have 6,000 citizens treated at medical clinics or hospitals in a single city.
Achievements.DESCRIPTION[TopoftheClass]: Build a city where at least 15% of the population has a university level of education.
Achievements.DESCRIPTION[WelcomeOneandAl: Have a total of 6,000 tourist visits in a single city.
Achievements.DESCRIPTION[Groundskeeper]: Built 10 Parks & Recreation buildings in a single city.
Achievements.DESCRIPTION[ZeroEmission]: Have a city that produces 500 MW electricity by only using renewable energy sources.
Achievements.DESCRIPTION[WideVariety]: Create 10 districts, each with its own unique set of policies in one city.
Assets.SUB_SERVICE_DESCRIPTION[RoadsSmal: Basic urban streets that allow for low speed traffic.

Assets.DESCRIPTION[Small Road Oneway - 3: Simple three-lane road that allows traffic in one direction.

Assets.DESCRIPTION[Medium Road Oneway -: Five-lane road that allows traffic in one direction.

Assets.DESCRIPTION[Highway Twoway - 2 la: Two-lane highway that allows traffic in both directions.

Assets.DESCRIPTION[Traffic Spawner]: Dev tool, not in final game
Assets.SUB_SERVICE_DESCRIPTION[Electrici: Electricity is one of the most important resources of a modern city. Power can be produced in various ways and each comes with its own pros and cons.
Assets.DESCRIPTION[Low-voltage Line]: Cables for transfering low voltage utility currents between locations.
Assets.DESCRIPTION[SmallCoalPowerPlant01: A basic power plant that burns coal to produce electricity. Low cost, but generates lots of pollution.
Assets.UPGRADE_DESCRIPTION[CoalPowerPlan: Increases the plant's fuel storage capacity.
Assets.SUB_SERVICE_DESCRIPTION[Water & S: Access to fresh water is important throughout the city. A network of buildings and pipes help deliver water to citizens and move sewage out.
Assets.UPGRADE_DESCRIPTION[GroundwaterPu: An additional pump that significantly increases water intake and delivery capacity.
A massive reservoir that stores water for later use during peak times or shortages.
Assets.DESCRIPTION[Combined Small Pipe]: Dual pipes that deliver both fresh water and sewage.
Assets.UPGRADE_DESCRIPTION[WaterPumpingS: A massive reservoir that stores water for later use during peak times or shortages.
An additional pump that significantly increases water intake and delivery capacity.
Assets.UPGRADE_DESCRIPTION[Hospital01 Sp: Specialized treatment helps citizens in the hospital's service area remain healthier.
Assets.DESCRIPTION[HealthResearchInstitu: A facility that studies the ways citizens can remain healthier and educates them in various ways, including lectures and outdoor challenges.
Assets.SUB_SERVICE_DESCRIPTION[Deathcare: At some point, every citizen's life comes to an end. Deathcare services take care of those who have passed on.
Assets.UPGRADE_DESCRIPTION[Cemetery01 Ma: A memorial tomb for a person of importance. The cemetery becomes a sightseeing attraction.
Assets.UPGRADE_DESCRIPTION[Cemetery01 Co: A set of walls for storing the cremated remains of the deceased.
Assets.UPGRADE_DESCRIPTION[Crematorium01: Increases the speed at which remains can be processed.
Extended cold storage allows storing more deceased citizens before cremation.
Assets.SUB_SERVICE_DESCRIPTION[GarbageMa: Households and companies produce waste every day. Garbage management services collect and dispose of waste material.
Assets.UPGRADE_DESCRIPTION[Landfill01 Ga: Enables the landfill to maintain a much larger fleet of trucks for garbage collection.
Assets.SUB_SERVICE_DESCRIPTION[Fire & Re: Fire is the most common high-risk threat to buildings in the city. The fire & rescue services help prevent and put out fires and rescue citizens from accidents and other emergencies.
Assets.UPGRADE_DESCRIPTION[FireStation01: On-site training facilities that help firefighters stay in top shape and thus extinguish fires more efficiently.
Specialized rescue service workers search for survivors in collapsed buildings.
Assets.SUB_SERVICE_DESCRIPTION[DisasterC: Despite all preparations, disasters can sometimes strike. The disaster control services help citizens when the worst case scenario becomes a reality.
Assets.DESCRIPTION[EarlyDisasterWarningS: The EDWS contains multiple high-end detection systems that can spot approaching natural disasters in advance. Citizens can thus seek shelter or prepare buildings for the disaster ahead of time. Prepared buildings suffer less structural damage in the disaster.
Assets.UPGRADE_DESCRIPTION[EmergencyShel: More efficient air circulation allows for more people to take shelter here.
Extended stores of rations allow citizens to remain in the shelter for longer.
Assets.DESCRIPTION[LargeEmergencyShelter: A massive shelter that has the space and provisions to house a significant number of citizens for an extended period of time during even the most dangerous of disasters. When an evacuation order is given, specialized buses are sent out from the shelter to collect citizens from the affected areas.
Assets.UPGRADE_DESCRIPTION[PoliceHeadqua: More cells to hold a larger number of apprehended criminals.
Assets.DESCRIPTION[CentralInvestigationB: The local headquarters for CIB agents. The Central Intelligence Bureau investigates severe criminal activity and apprehends criminals with superior efficiency. The sole existence of the office lowers crime rate citywide.
Assets.SUB_SERVICE_DESCRIPTION[Education: The level of education affects every aspect of citizens' lives from jobs to consumption habits and garbage production. Education services provide schooling for kids, teens and adults alike.
Assets.UPGRADE_DESCRIPTION[ElementarySch: An attached clinic that helps children recover from injuries.
The activities provided by the playground bring increased well-being to citizens.
Assets.UPGRADE_DESCRIPTION[HighSchool01: The school is enlarged to make room for more students.
The perfect place for students and surrounding citizens to improve on their health.
The library, with its extended selection of textbooks, provides students with better chances of graduating.
Assets.UPGRADE_DESCRIPTION[College01 Ext: Provides further room for even more eager learners.
Assets.UPGRADE_DESCRIPTION[College01 Lib: The library, with its extended selection of textbooks, provides students with better chances of graduating.
Assets.UPGRADE_DESCRIPTION[University01: An extension to the facilities that houses even more classrooms and lecture halls.
A huge library that stores vast amounts of knowledge and thus increases the students' chances of graduating.
A park that grants nearby citizens both increased well-being as well as health.
Assets.UPGRADE_DESCRIPTION[TechnicalUniv: Improved practical learning that increases the students' chances of graduating.
Assets.UPGRADE_DESCRIPTION[MedicalUniver: Increased capacity for even more students.
Research work increases the students' chances of graduating.
Citizens near the university can be treated here and gain a boost to their health.
Assets.SUB_SERVICE_DESCRIPTION[Research]: Research facilities help in utilizing natural resources and aid advanced level students in their studies.
Assets.DESCRIPTION[GeologicalResearchCen: A facility for performing geological research and field studies. Helps discover larger underground deposits of ore and oil.
Assets.SUB_SERVICE_DESCRIPTION[Transport: Buses and taxis offer citizens a comfortable alternative to driving. Intercity buses transport citizens and tourists between cities.
Assets.UPGRADE_DESCRIPTION[BusDepot01 Ex: An extended garage that can house more buses.
Assets.DESCRIPTION[Bus Stop]: Buses stop to pick up and drop off passengers at the stops.
Assets.UPGRADE_DESCRIPTION[BusStation01: A built-in stop that allows for taxis to pick up and drop off customers directly at the station.
Adds more platforms to the station, allowing for increased amount of traffic.
Assets.DESCRIPTION[Double Train Track]: Double track that allows trains to run in both directions simultaneously.
Assets.DESCRIPTION[Passenger Train Line]: Connects train stations to create a passenger railway line.
Assets.UPGRADE_DESCRIPTION[TrainStation0: An extension that connects to the subway network. Works as a subway station.
A built-in stop that allows taxis to pick up and drop off customers directly at the station.
Assets.UPGRADE_DESCRIPTION[CargoTrainTer: Additional space that can be used to store even more cargo before it is sent forward.
Assets.DESCRIPTION[Oneway Train Track]: Single track that allows train traffic to run in one direction at a time.
Assets.UPGRADE_DESCRIPTION[RailYard01 Ma: Dedicated facilities that make train maintenance faster.
Assets.SUB_SERVICE_DESCRIPTION[Transport: Urban railway travel with trams is a handy addition or alternative to other public transport methods.
Assets.DESCRIPTION[Tram Line]: Connects tram stops to create a tram line.
Assets.DESCRIPTION[Tram Stop]: Trams pick up and drop off passengers at the stops.
Assets.DESCRIPTION[Double Subway Track]: Double track that allows subway trains to run in both directions simultaneously.
Assets.DESCRIPTION[Subway Line]: Connect subway stations to create a subway line.
Assets.DESCRIPTION[Oneway Subway Track]: Single track that allows subway train traffic to run in one direction at a time.
Assets.UPGRADE_DESCRIPTION[Harbor01 Extr: An additional pier that allows for another ship to dock.
Assets.UPGRADE_DESCRIPTION[CargoHarbor01: Allows for trains to transport cargo directly to and from the harbor.
Additional cranes help to increase the speed at which loading and unloading takes place.
Extended warehouses allow for more cargo to be stored.
Assets.UPGRADE_DESCRIPTION[Airport01 Bus: Business travelers have an easier time at the Airport. Increases the attractiveness of the city.
Assets.UPGRADE_DESCRIPTION[Airport01 Car: Provides storage space for cargo, and the integrated rail tracks and the truck terminal allow for cargo traffic to flow with ease.
Assets.DESCRIPTION[SpaceCenter01]: A huge facility that houses both a space museum as well as an active command center and rocket launch platform. The combination of history and the unique sight of rocket launches attracts tourists and increases the effectiveness of industries and offices.
Assets.DESCRIPTION[Terrain Soften Tool]: Evens the elevation differences in the affected area making the slopes smoother by removing any steep precipices or rough terrain.
Assets.DESCRIPTION[Terrain Level Tool]: Levels the terrain to a certain height.
Assets.DESCRIPTION[Terrain Slope Tool]: Creates a slope by evening out the terrain height between the terraformed area and the target height.
Assets.DESCRIPTION[Pavement Path]: A paved path that connects seamlessly with the sidewalks of roads.
Assets.SUB_SERVICE_DESCRIPTION[Parks & R: Making the city a more pleasant place to live in is easily done by dedicating some areas to parks and attractions.
Assets.UPGRADE_DESCRIPTION[ParkMaintenan: Increased space to house more vehicles.
The increased availability of supplies allows the maintenance vehicles to work for longer.
Assets.DESCRIPTION[WaterPark01]: An amusement park that offers plenty of water related activities for children and grown-ups alike.
Assets.SUB_SERVICE_DESCRIPTION[Communica: Letters, parcels and other mail is handled by the post service.
Assets.DESCRIPTION[PostMailbox01]: Boxes used by citizens to send out their mail. Post office vehicles pick up the mail periodically.
Assets.UPGRADE_DESCRIPTION[PostOffice01: Increased space to house more post vans.
Extended storage space helps store more mail.
Assets.UPGRADE_DESCRIPTION[PostSortingFa: Increased space allows for more mail trucks to run.
Extended storage space helps store more mail.
Assets.SUB_SERVICE_DESCRIPTION[Communica: Moving beyond basic radio and television services can be achieved by investing in advanced telecom facilities.
Assets.UPGRADE_DESCRIPTION[RadioMast01 W: An antenna extension that increases the network coverage area of the mast.
Assets.DESCRIPTION[SatelliteUplink01]: Transmits all sorts of data globally. Information and entertainment can be sent to and received from the other side of the world. Increases the capacity of the network and increases entertainment in the whole city.
Assets.DESCRIPTION[TelecomTower01]: The center for media broadcasts, telecommunications and long range cellular networks. Also houses local media headquarters.
Assets.SUB_SERVICE_DESCRIPTION[ZonesResi: The residential zones are for various types of housing.
Assets.DESCRIPTION[EU Residential Low]: European style single and and semi-detached houses.
Assets.DESCRIPTION[Residential LowRent]: Large apartment buildings with small, affordable apartments. The lower rents provide lower tax income as a result.
Assets.DESCRIPTION[NA Residential Low]: North American style single and and semi-detached houses.
Assets.SUB_SERVICE_DESCRIPTION[ZonesComm: The commercial zones are for various types of businesses and services.
Assets.DESCRIPTION[Industrial Manufactur: Workshops and factories, warehouses and storage yards.
Assets.UPGRADE_DESCRIPTION[SubwayYard01: Increased capacity for more subway trains.
Dedicated facilities that make subway train maintenance faster.
Assets.UPGRADE_DESCRIPTION[WindTurbine01: A solar panel that increases power output during daytime.
Assets.UPGRADE_DESCRIPTION[Landfill01 Wa: Processing the incoming waste and recycling what's possible lowers the ground pollution produced by the landfill site.
Assets.UPGRADE_DESCRIPTION[RecyclingCent: Enables the center to maintain a much larger fleet of trucks for garbage collection.
Allows for significantly larger amounts of garbage to be stored for processing.
Assets.DESCRIPTION[HazardousWasteProcess: A specialized facility for collecting and handling the most hazardous and toxic waste products that result from industrial production. As these dangerous substances are collected away, the ground pollution produced by all industrial buildings is lowered.
Assets.UPGRADE_DESCRIPTION[WastewaterTre: Provides increased processing capacity for the facility.
Assets.UPGRADE_DESCRIPTION[IncinerationP: Enables the plant to maintain a much larger fleet of trucks for garbage collection.
Provides an increase in the waste burning and energy production capacity.
Allows for significantly larger amounts of garbage to be stored for burning.
Assets.UPGRADE_DESCRIPTION[RadioMast01 B: Enhances the network significantly and allows it to handle much more traffic.
Assets.UPGRADE_DESCRIPTION[ServerFarm01: Increases the coverage area of the server farm.
State-of-the-art machines with high computing power remarkably increase network capacity.
Assets.DESCRIPTION[Covered Pedestrian Br: The bridge deck is covered by a roof, which is held up by a lattice structure on the sides.
Assets.DESCRIPTION[Arc Pedestrian Bridge: Support cables hanging from arches hold the bridge deck.
Assets.DESCRIPTION[Cable Stayed Pedestri: Support cables run from upright towers in a fan-like pattern directly to the bridge deck.
Assets.DESCRIPTION[Suspension Bridge - H: Suspension cables run between support towers, and vertical suspension cables hold the bridge deck.
Assets.DESCRIPTION[Tied Arch Bridge - 4: An arch held in shape by tying chords sits above the bridge, and supporting hangers running down from the arch hold the bridge deck.
Assets.DESCRIPTION[Cable Stayed Bridge -: Support cables run from upright towers in a fan-like pattern directly to the bridge deck.
Assets.DESCRIPTION[Truss Arch Bridge - 4: An arch under the bridge supports trusses, which in turn hold the bridge deck.
Assets.DESCRIPTION[Extradosed Bridge - 4: Support cables run from short support towers to the bridge superstructure.
Support cables run from short support towers to the bridge superstructure. A wide median runs along the middle.
Assets.DESCRIPTION[Suspension Bridge - M: Suspension cables run between support towers, and vertical suspension cables hold the bridge deck.
Assets.DESCRIPTION[Cable-Stayed Bridge -: Support cables run from upright towers in a fan-like pattern directly to the bridge deck.
Assets.UPGRADE_DESCRIPTION[Hospital01 He: Medical helicopters operating from here deliver patients by air. They transport people for treatment from accident sites and remote locations.
Assets.DESCRIPTION[FirewatchTower01]:
A tower that keeps a constant lookout, reducing the chance of forest fires and alerting firefighters if a fire does break out.
Does not need a road connection, but requires electricity to function.
Assets.UPGRADE_DESCRIPTION[GroundwaterPu: Greatly reduces the amount of pollutants in the intake water.
Assets.UPGRADE_DESCRIPTION[WaterTower01: A platform on the top of the water tower allows for sightseeing and thus provides the tower with entertainment value.
An extra pump that increases water intake capacity.
Assets.UPGRADE_DESCRIPTION[SewageOutlet0: Reduces the amount of pollutants in the water before it is expelled into the environment.
Assets.UPGRADE_DESCRIPTION[Harbor01 Tran: An integrated bus station and taxi stand that allows direct bus and taxi traffic to and from the harbor.
Assets.UPGRADE_DESCRIPTION[TaxiDepot01 E: One fourth of the taxi fleet is replaced with electric taxis.
Assets.UPGRADE_DESCRIPTION[TaxiDepot01 D: Allows taxis to pick up passengers from all over the city, not just dedicated taxi stands.
Assets.UPGRADE_DESCRIPTION[EmergencyBatt: Allows for an extra Power Line to be connected to the station.
Assets.UPGRADE_DESCRIPTION[GasPowerPlant: A more efficient burn process allows the same power output with less fuel.
Assets.DESCRIPTION[Signature Buildings]: Special unlockable buildings that provide various benefits to their surroundings.
Assets.DESCRIPTION[Landmarks]: Famous landmarks from around the world that you can add to your city.
Assets.SUB_SERVICE_DESCRIPTION[Signature: Signature buildings relating to residential zoning.
Signature buildings relating to commercial zoning.
Signature buildings relating to industrial zoning.
Signature buildings relating to office zoning.
A collection of landmarks from around the world.
Assets.DESCRIPTION[NA Residential Mixed]: North American style apartment buildings with commercial space on the bottom and apartments on top.
Assets.DESCRIPTION[NA Residential High]: North American style large apartment buildings.
Assets.DESCRIPTION[EU Residential Mixed]: European style apartment buildings with commercial space on the bottom and apartments on top.
Assets.DESCRIPTION[EU Commercial High]: European style supermarkets, malls, hotels, big movie theaters, concert halls, theaters, fitness centers, department stores.
Assets.DESCRIPTION[EU Commercial Low]: European style stores, boutiques, gas stations, supermarkets, restaurants, motels, bars, travel agencies.
Assets.DESCRIPTION[NA Commercial High]: North American style supermarkets, malls, hotels, big movie theaters, concert halls, theaters, fitness centers, department stores.
Assets.DESCRIPTION[NA Commercial Low]: North American style stores, boutiques, gas stations, supermarkets, restaurants, motels, bars, travel agencies.
Assets.DESCRIPTION[EU_ResidentialLowSign: The terrace of this house is perfect for the parties the pop star living here loves to throw.
When not on stage, this is where a noteworthy thespian relaxes.
The shapes of this mansion reflect the art of the sculptor who owns it.
Assets.DESCRIPTION[NA_ResidentialLowSign: A famous rock star lives in this mansion when not on tour.
The place where a star of the silver screen withdraws to get a break from the busy world outside.
This painter is known the world over, but chooses to live in this city.
Assets.DESCRIPTION[EU_ResidentialHighSig: The beautiful wavy design of this massive residential building catches the light and the eye in the most fascinating way.
The residents of Halo Heights are able to touch the skies. Luxurious homes for those who aim for the top. The grand design improves the mood of passers-by and attracts tourists.
A round, terraced residential building complex that elicits feelings of triumph of both its residents as well as everyone around.
Assets.DESCRIPTION[NA_MixedSignature01]: Books to nourish the mind and soul, with luxury apartments on top. The bottom floor bookstore stocks everything from the ordinary to the esoteric.
Assets.DESCRIPTION[NA_MixedSignature03]: Bespoke suits and dresses are made in the bottom floor tailor shop, while high-end residences fill the upper floors.
Assets.DESCRIPTION[EU_ResidentialMediumR: Citizens will be dizzy with excitement living here!
This beautiful old style building lifts the spirits of everyone passing by.
Assets.DESCRIPTION[EU_MixedSignature01]: Luxurious living spaces atop a high-end restaurant. Made for those who appreciate life for its pleasures.
Assets.DESCRIPTION[EU_MixedSignature02]: Art and high-end housing go hand in hand in this building. A multi-floored gallery space at the bottom is completed by luxury residences above.
Assets.DESCRIPTION[EU_MixedSignature03]: Life is all about fun and games in this residential building that houses a famous toy store on the bottom floor.
Assets.DESCRIPTION[NA_ResidentialMediumS: Residents will enjoy the atmosphere of this smooth, luxurious building.
Luxuriously stylized brick building that has many visually inspiring aspects.
A highly decorated residential building whose tower designs invoke the feeling of magic and fantasy in its residents and everyone nearby.
Assets.DESCRIPTION[NA_ResidentialMediumR: A stone monolith that diversifies and enhances its surroundings.
Brilliant moods and beautiful design despite some issues with windows.
An exquisitely decorated red brick building that celebrates its developer's first decade in the business and radiates warm and welcoming vibes.
Assets.DESCRIPTION[EU_ResidentialMediumS: A modern classic that puts a smile on the faces of its inhabitants.
An old factory converted into luxurious living spaces that spark joy in their inhabitants.
The smooth, arched shapes simply boggle the mind of everyone around. But in a good way.
Assets.DESCRIPTION[NA_ResidentialHighSig: A residential glass-walled monolith that reaches almost impossibly high into the sky.
Old styled luxurious residential skyscraper building with a castle-like construction on top. Lifts peoples' spirits and attracts tourists.
A modern glass and steel skyscraper with a curious, angular design.
Assets.DESCRIPTION[Nasinneula]: Näsinneula is an observation tower in Tampere, Finland. Opened in 1971, the tower is located in the Särkänniemi amusement park, overseeing Lake Näsijärvi. A revolving restaurant is located in the top of the tower, with one revolution taking 45 minutes.
Assets.DESCRIPTION[NationalGalleryofArts: A national art museum in Washington, D.C. Established in 1937, the museum is open to the public and free of charge.
Assets.DESCRIPTION[BotanicalGarden01]: A huge greenhouse that displays wondrous plantlife from all over the globe.
Assets.DESCRIPTION[FountainPlaza01]: A massive, round plaza with concentric fountains.
Assets.DESCRIPTION[GrandHotel01]: A towering, monumental hotel with a classic design that's stood the test of time.
Assets.DESCRIPTION[Extractor Lot]: Adjusts the area of the specialized industry.
Assets.DESCRIPTION[OldCastle01]: A restored medieval castle open for visitors.
Assets.DESCRIPTION[NotreDame]: Notre-Dame de Paris is the world-famous French medieval Gothic cathedral. Built over the years from 1163 to 1345, it has become one of the most widely recognized symbols of the city of Paris.
Assets.DESCRIPTION[City Budget]: The panel displays a breakdown of all the sources of income and expenditure the city has, and also allows you to take out loans.
Assets.DESCRIPTION[Taxation]: The panel allows for the adjustment of the various taxes citizens, companies and businesses pay.
Assets.DESCRIPTION[Natural Disasters]: Natural disasters are special events that may strike the city and wreak different kinds of havoc. They can result from different environmental factors. Warning systems and broadcasts can be used to inform the public, and emergency shelters help citizens cope when a disaster strikes.
Assets.DESCRIPTION[Production Panel]: The panel displays data about the production and consumption of resources throughout the city.
Assets.DESCRIPTION[Service Budgets]: City Service budgets can be lowered if needed to save on expenses. However, as less money is directed towards a service, its quality also suffers.
Assets.DESCRIPTION[Trade]: Resources and some City Services can be imported and exported as required. Resource trade happens automatically between citizens and companies and the outside world, while City Service trade can be limited by adjusting relevant budgets.
Assets.SUB_SERVICE_DESCRIPTION[ZonesOffi: The office zones are for various types of office buildings.
Assets.SUB_SERVICE_DESCRIPTION[ZonesIndu: The industrial zones are for various types of industrial buildings.

Assets.DESCRIPTION[Grand Bridge]: Highly decorated, large support towers with walkways between tie together heavy suspension cables that hold the bridge deck.
Assets.DESCRIPTION[Golden Gate Bridge]: Originally located in San Francisco, this famous suspension bridge opened in 1937 and spans the strait that connects the San Francisco Bay to the Pacific Ocean.
Assets.DESCRIPTION[Small Road Asymmetric: Two lanes going one way and one in the other. Works well especially for turning lanes in an intersection.
Assets.DESCRIPTION[Medium Road Asymmetri: Three lanes going one way and two in the other. Works well especially for turning lanes in an intersection.
Assets.DESCRIPTION[Large Road Asymmetric: Four lanes going one way and three in the other. Works well especially for turning lanes in an intersection.
Assets.DESCRIPTION[Large Road Oneway]: Six-lane road that allows traffic in one direction.
Assets.DESCRIPTION[Large Road Oneway - 7: Seven-lane road that allows traffic in one direction.
Assets.DESCRIPTION[HydroelectricPowerPla: A dam that spans a river and produces electricity by harnessing the flow of water with turbines.
Assets.DESCRIPTION[Double Public Transpo: Two road lanes going in opposite directions, dedicated to public transport, emergency vehicles and turning traffic. Can be added to existing roads with the **Replace** Tool Mode.
Assets.DESCRIPTION[Oneway Public Transpo: Single, one-way lane dedicated to public transport, emergency vehicles and turning traffic. Can be added to existing roads with the **Replace** Tool Mode.
Assets.UPGRADE_DESCRIPTION[CoalPowerPlan: A more efficient burn process allows the same power output with less fuel.
Assets.UPGRADE_DESCRIPTION[WindTurbine01: Upgraded systems allow for a significant increase in power output.
Assets.UPGRADE_DESCRIPTION[Heliport01 Me: Improved maintenance facilities for medical helicopters. Allows them to get back into action quicker.
Assets.UPGRADE_DESCRIPTION[Heliport01 Po: Improved maintenance facilities for police helicopters. Allows them to get back into action quicker.
Assets.UPGRADE_DESCRIPTION[Heliport01 Fi: Improved maintenance facilities for firefighting helicopters. Allows them to get back into action quicker.
Assets.DESCRIPTION[CoalPowerPlant01]:
A power plant that burns coal to produce electricity. Fairly inexpensive to build and maintain, but generates lots of pollution.
Can be upgraded with an additional turbine, enlarged coal storage, exhaust filter and an advanced furnace.
Assets.DESCRIPTION[RoadMaintenanceDepot0:
Base of operations for road maintenance personnel, their tools and vehicles. Road maintenance comprises road repairs, snow clearing, and traffic accident clean-up.
Can be upgraded with an extra garage for a larger maintenance vehicle fleet.
Assets.DESCRIPTION[WindTurbine01]:

Assets.DESCRIPTION[DesalinationPlant01]: Extracts water from lakes, rivers and other bodies of surface water and pumps it to the city's water network. This high-power facility can easily perform the work of several regular pumping stations on its own.
Assets.NAME[ServiceBuildingDesalinationP: Service Building Advanced Water Pumping Station
Assets.DESCRIPTION[EU_CommercialLowSigna: An old style soda bar with a large rooftop terrace where patrons can enjoy their beverage while taking in the sights.
A fancy, modern building that is sure to cater to any and all motor vehicle needs.
This large marketplace can handle rush hour influx of customers with ease.
Assets.DESCRIPTION[NA_CommercialLowSigna: A classic American style diner building for when you just want some nostalgia.
Room for all the hungry customers under one roof.
A large gas station and rest stop for motorist.
Assets.DESCRIPTION[EU_CommercialHighSign: A large retail space for all your citizens' retail needs.
The destination for recreation. A massive building that can hold even the largest gathering of family and friends.
A classically designed green roof building with office space. An architectural landmark that attracts tourists far and wide.
Assets.DESCRIPTION[NA_CommercialHighSign: Modern fashion needs are served by this center for fashion.
A visually striking old style building with marble decorations. Guarantees service satisfaction to all the tourists it attracts.
A massive center for all your electronics needs. They stock items so rare that people from other cities come to visit just to get their hands on the latest hardware.
Assets.DESCRIPTION[IndustrialManufacturi: The cars of tomorrow are being built in this megafactory today!
Crushing large rocks into ever smaller rocks like never before.
Paper for all purposes, it's all made here!
Fuel production of all types happens here.
From the humble toaster to the self-organizing sock drawer, this factory makes everything that runs on electricity.
Pharmaceutical production, endeavouring to make the products accessible to all.
Oil that once just used to uselessly lie underground is fashioned into many different substances in this very refinery!
Assets.DESCRIPTION[OfficeLowSignature01]: The companies working in this modern office building not only make sure that justice is served, but their efficiency actually helps to reduce the crime rate in the neighborhood.
Assets.DESCRIPTION[OfficeLowSignature02]: A modern office building where coffee gets converted into game design, art, and code.
Assets.DESCRIPTION[OfficeLowSignature03]: In this complex office building you can often hear people muttering the motto, better safe than sorry and just in case.
Assets.DESCRIPTION[OfficeHighSignature01: True to a classical style, this office building houses media companies that provide entertainment, information and everything in between. Its looks attract tourists that appreciate a timeless classic.
Assets.DESCRIPTION[OfficeHighSignature02: Design, form and function tied together, makes this the ideal place to make games, software and more. The visually stunning exterior also attracts tourists from the outside.
Assets.DESCRIPTION[OfficeHighSignature03: A tower that truly leaves its mark on the city. It Houses a media company that has made many artists famous, which attracts tourists from all over the world.
Assets.SUB_SERVICE_DESCRIPTION[Vegetatio: Trees and bushes to decorate the city.
Assets.SUB_SERVICE_DESCRIPTION[Pathways]: Paths that can be used by pedestrians.
Assets.UPGRADE_DESCRIPTION[Prison01 Pris: Increases the prisoners’ Wellbeing and prepares them for the life outside of the prison walls.
Assets.UPGRADE_DESCRIPTION[Prison01 Extr: Increases the number of prisoners that can be housed in the prison.
Assets.DESCRIPTION[Prison01]:
Houses convicted criminals.

Can be upgraded with a prison library and recreation center and additional wings for increased prisoner capacity.
Assets.DESCRIPTION[FerrisWheel01]: The Ferris Wheel is a giant observation wheel and it is an extremely popular tourist attraction in the city.
Assets.UPGRADE_DESCRIPTION[Cemetery01 Ch: A small place of reverence. Provides increased well-being.
Assets.SUB_SERVICE_DESCRIPTION[Administr: Where there are people, there's paperwork. Administration facilities help both citizens and businesses to prosper in the city.
Assets.DESCRIPTION[WelfareOffice01]: Helps the less fortunate by increasing well-being in the surrounding neighborhood.
Assets.SUB_SERVICE_DESCRIPTION[Police]: Crime is a problem facing every larger community. An active police force reduces crime probability and keeps criminals at bay.
Assets.SUB_SERVICE_DESCRIPTION[Transport: Transporting people and cargo on tracks is a viable method of mass transit. It's fast and efficient.

When the surface begins to become crowded, transport can be taken underground. And while a subway can be built overground as well as underground, its strength lies in transportation of large numbers of people below the ground without taking up valuable land.
Ships can move massive amounts of cargo and huge numbers of people from one port to another.
Assets.UPGRADE_DESCRIPTION[PostSortingFa: Mail is sorted more accurately, so trucks only carry the essential items for each run. Results in increased sorting speed.
Assets.DESCRIPTION[GasPowerPlant01]:
A power plant fueled by natural gas. Larger and more efficient than Coal Power Plants with slightly less pollution. Fairly cost effective to build and maintain, although running costs depend on the price of the fossil fuel.
Can be upgraded with an additional turbine, enlarged fuel storage, exhaust filter and an advanced furnace.
Assets.DESCRIPTION[NuclearPowerPlant01]: A thermal power plant that uses nuclear fission as the source of heat. Generates vast amounts of power and requires lots of water for cooling. Both the building and upkeep costs are rather high. Generates a lot of noise pollution but no ground or air pollution.
Assets.DESCRIPTION[NA_MixedSignature02]: Luxury homes on top of a clothing store. With an updating wardrobe downstairs, every day can be full of style and sass!
Assets.DESCRIPTION[EU_ResidentialMediumR: The stars smile down on the residents of Constellation Apartments.
Assets.DESCRIPTION[Cemetery01]:
The final resting place for deceased citizens. Cemeteries collect and transport the dead with hearses.
Can be upgraded with a temple, a mausoleum, and a columbarium.
Assets.DESCRIPTION[GymPark01]: Citizens work on their physique and tan here at the same time.
Assets.DESCRIPTION[Hospital01]:
Provides health care for a large area and takes care of sick and injured citizens. Keeps citizens in its service area healthier.
Can be upgraded with medical helicopters, a trauma center, and a specialized treatment ward.
Assets.DESCRIPTION[Agriculture Area Plac: The Textile Fiber Farming specialized industry can be set up on areas of Fertile Land to produce textile fibers.
Assets.NAME[ServiceBuildingHospitalSpeci: Service Building Hospital Specialized Treatment Ward Upgrade
Assets.NAME[PrisonExtraWingUpgrade]: Service Building Prison Extra Wing Upgrade
Assets.DESCRIPTION[IndustrialManufacturi: Chemicals are everything and more are made here everyday!

Assets.DESCRIPTION[NA_BusStop02]: A North American style bus stop with walls, roof and seats. Requires a road with a sidewalk.
Assets.UPGRADE_DESCRIPTION[BusStation01:
Provides further charging capacity for electric buses, which increases their range significantly.
The Electric Bus Maintenance Upgrade at the Bus Depot enables electric buses.
Assets.UPGRADE_DESCRIPTION[SewageOutlet0: Reduces the amount of contaminants in the sewage being expelled.
Assets.UPGRADE_DESCRIPTION[PoliceHeadqua: Police helicopters operating from here patrol the city from the skies. They can cover larger areas and respond faster than patrol cars.
Assets.DESCRIPTION[NA Residential Low Wa: North American style single-detached waterfront houses.
Assets.DESCRIPTION[EU_ResidentialLowWate: A villa fit for extreme athletes. It has everything a sports enthusiast would ever want.
When the golfer who lives here is not practicing their drive, the residents in the vicinity can safely stand in awe at the sight of this mansion.
One does not have to be royal to feel like one when living in this castle-like classical mansion. Just the mere presence of this building increases the well-being of its nearby residents.
Assets.DESCRIPTION[NA_ResidentialLowWate: Charming, has potential and originally below market value aka the perfect holiday home of a successful real-estate agent. Residents in the vicinity can just feel their well-being increase.
Truly a building made by an architect, for an architect. The ingenuity of architectural styles, strong lines and bold shapes inspire its nearby residents, increasing their well-being.

With its many wings and stories and imported interior decorations, this mansion has everything a shipping industry mogul could wish for. The presence of this building increases the well-being of nearby residents.

Assets.DESCRIPTION[FloridaPalmTree01]: Florida palm trees are large palm trees that have been planted throughout the tropics and subtropics as ornamental trees.
Assets.DESCRIPTION[RoyalPalmTree01]: Royal palm trees are usually planted as ornamental trees and also used for lumber. They are native to Central America.
Assets.DESCRIPTION[SylvesterPalmTree01]: Sylvester palm trees are flowering trees that produce fruit which used to make beverages and fruit preserves. They are native to South Asia.

A place of basic education for children. Provides the first level of education.
Can be upgraded with an extension wing and gymnasium.

Chirper.FIRST_POWER_PLANT:0: Hooray, we have power! <{LINK_TARGET_0}|This power plant> is pumping out electricity! #power
Chirper.HOUSING_SHORTAGE:0: The #housing #market stinks. Where do I complain? So I'd like to live in this city, but there are no #homes available. What gives?
Chirper.HOUSING_SHORTAGE:1: Uh, hello? I'd like to live somewhere. Like a #building?
Chirper.HOUSING_SHORTAGE:2: Anyone else notice there's no #housing available anywhere?
Chirper.HOUSING_SHORTAGE:3: We could really use some more #residential #buildings in the city right about now!
Chirper.HOUSING_SHORTAGE:4: I'd really like to have a #home here in the city, but there are none available. What gives?
Chirper.NO_ELECTRICITY:0: What's going on with the power? How am I supposed to chirp without electricity?
Chirper.NO_ELECTRICITY:2: Oh no, the #power is out. I wonder how long my battery lasts.
Chirper.NO_ELECTRICITY:3: Why is it dark in here all of a sudden? Turn the #power back on!
Chirper.NO_ELECTRICITY:4: Is the #powerplant offline or something? I need #electricity!
Chirper.NO_WATER:0: Erm, there's no #water coming from the tap. What's up?
Chirper.NO_WATER:1: Suddenly I'm not getting any #water in here. Weird.
Chirper.NO_WATER:2: What's up with the #water? I'm getting nothing here.
Chirper.NO_WATER:3: Someone turn the #water back on, please?
Chirper.NO_WATER:4: I'm trying to take a shower here and suddenly there's no #water?
Chirper.DIRTY_WATER:0: I'm no expert, but I'm pretty sure #water isn't supposed to be brown. #yuck
Chirper.DIRTY_WATER:1: What is this #sludge coming out of my water tap?
Chirper.DIRTY_WATER:2: Eugh. The water from my tap #stinks! What's up?
Chirper.DIRTY_WATER:3: Ok this #water certainly is far from #clean. Somebody do something?
Chirper.GARBAGE_PILING_UP:0: I need to hold my nose when I'm out. Pick up the #garbage already!
Chirper.GARBAGE_PILING_UP:1: Somebody do something about the #stinky #garbage lying around.
Chirper.GARBAGE_PILING_UP:2: Why isn't anyone picking up the #garbage?
Chirper.GARBAGE_PILING_UP:3: I haven't seen a #garbage #truck here in ages! What gives?
Chirper.GARBAGE_PILING_UP:4: I really wish someone would come around to collect the #garbage. It's stinking everything up!
Chirper.RESIDENTIAL_LEVEL_UP:0: I'm in love with how our #improved #homes look!
Chirper.COMMERCIAL_LEVEL_UP:0: I'm seeing plenty of good looking #luxury #items. Gonna find me a good deal!
Chirper.COMMERCIAL_LEVEL_DOWN:0: Where's all the #cool #stuff gone, what's going on with the #fancy #shops?
Chirper.INDUSTRIAL_LEVEL_UP:0: Plenty of open #jobs in the #industry sector! PM me for details!
Chirper.INDUSTRIAL_LEVEL_DOWN:0: Industries are going bust left and right! So many friends are out of jobs. #sad
Chirper.OFFICE_LEVEL_UP:0: Check out these fancy new #office spaces!
Chirper.MOSTLY_SUNNY_WEATHER:0: Does anyone else just praise the #sun?
Chirper.MOSTLY_SUNNY_WEATHER:1: I love all the #sunlight we are getting!
Chirper.MOSTLY_CLOUDY_WEATHER:0: At least the sun won't get in my eye with all these #clouds
Chirper.MOSTLY_CLOUDY_WEATHER:1: It seems it's #overcast weather again. Well, good for taking photos outside!
Chirper.MOSTLY_RAINY_WEATHER:0: It can't #rain all the time. I hope.
Chirper.MOSTLY_RAINY_WEATHER:2: I love the rain! Makes the #air feel #cleaner
Chirper.MOSTLY_STORMY_WEATHER:0: Bring it on! Love me a good #storm
Chirper.LOWEST_TEMP_20:0: Is it just me or is it seriously #hot out there? Somebody crank up the A/C!
Chirper.LOWEST_TEMP_20:1: I'm literally #melting in this heat. What a world.
Chirper.LOWEST_TEMP_15:0: Such a nice, balmy weather. Perfect for enjoying the #outdoors
Chirper.LOWEST_TEMP_15:1: I love warm weather! I hope it is not going to rain today!
Chirper.HIGHEST_TEMP_15:0: Didn't think I'd need a jacket today, but it's feeling a bit too #chilly for my taste
Chirper.HIGHEST_TEMP_15:1: I just love this weather! Not too hot, not too cold! #perfect
Chirper.HIGHEST_TEMP_NEG_15:0: Why so cold? I'm wearing six layers and still #freezing :(
Chirper.HIGHEST_TEMP_NEG_15:1: Enjoy winter when you can! Soon it will be too hot!
Chirper.TOURISM_UP_20:0: So many new faces on the streets of our fine city! #yaytourism
Chirper.TOURISM_DOWN_20:0: Where have all the #tourists gone? It used to be so lively and now it's just... quiet.
Chirper.CRIME_RATE_HIGH:0: Afraid to go out at night #fixthecrimeproblem
Chirper.CRIME_RATE_HIGH:1: Street thugs and roaming gangs. What is this, the #postapocalypse?
Chirper.UNEMPLOYMENT_RATE_HIGH:0: Plz with a #job soon? I've been waiting for so long already

EconomyPanel.SERVICE_DESCRIPTION[Communi: Lowering the Communications Service budget will result in reduced network capacity and post vehicle capacity.
EconomyPanel.SERVICE_DESCRIPTION[Educati: Lowering the Education Service budget will result in fewer students graduating.
EconomyPanel.SERVICE_DESCRIPTION[Electri: Lowering the Electricity Service budget will result in reduced power output levels.
EconomyPanel.SERVICE_DESCRIPTION[Fire &: Lowering the Fire & Rescue Service budget will result in reduced rescue vehicle capacity and shelter capacity.
EconomyPanel.SERVICE_DESCRIPTION[Garbage: Lowering the Garbage Management Service budget will result in reduced vehicle capacity and processing speed.
EconomyPanel.SERVICE_DESCRIPTION[Health: Lowering the Healthcare Service budget will lower the treatment bonuses as well as the number of Healthcare vehicles.
EconomyPanel.SERVICE_DESCRIPTION[Parks &: Lowering the Parks & Recreation Service budget will reduce the attractiveness and entertainment values of parks, plazas, recreational facilities and tourist attractions.

EconomyPanel.SERVICE_DESCRIPTION[Transpo: Lowering the Transportation Service budget will result in lowered vehicle capacity and longer maintenance times.
EconomyPanel.SERVICE_DESCRIPTION[Water &: Lowering the Water & Sewage Service budget will result in lowered pumping station processing capacity.
EconomyPanel.LOAN_PAGE_DESCRIPTION:
If your are short on money, you can take a loan to finance the expansion of your city.

In return, you will have to pay **interest** every month until you repay the loan by moving the loan slider back to 0.

Your **borrowing limit** will increase with every milestone. The closer you get to the limit, the higher the **interest rate** will be.

The interest rate can be decreased by placing a **City Hall** or **Central Bank** in city.
EconomyPanel.LOAN_CHART_RELATIVE_COST: Share of the city's monthly income spent on loan interest: **{RELATIVE_LOAN_COST}**
EconomyPanel.LOAN_CHART_BUDGET_WARNING: The city's monthly expenses are exceeding the available income! To avoid your budget from spiraling out of control, consider paying back some or all of your loan, increase taxes, or reduce the current amount of expenses.
EconomyPanel.LOAN_CHART_BUDGET_WARNING_M: The city's monthly expenses will soon exceed the available income! Consider reducing the loan or raising taxes to increase the city's income.

EconomyPanel.SERVICES_RESOURCE_FEE_DESCR:
Citizens and businesses pay a service fee for using electricity, which offsets some of its production cost.

The electricity service fee affects the **overall electricity consumption rate** of the city. It also affects the happiness of citizens and companies' ability to do business.

Citizens and businesses pay a service fee for using water, which offsets some its production cost.

The water service fee affects the **overall water consumption rate** and **sewage generation** of the city. It also affects the happiness of citizens and companies' ability to do business.
EconomyPanel.TAX_AREA_DESCRIPTION[Reside:
Residential taxes are collected from citizens' monthly wages.

Tax rates can be set individually based on each citizen education level.

Low taxes encourage citizens to move into the city. Lower taxes also help residential buildings level up faster, since more money is left over after upkeep expenses are paid.

Higher taxes bring more money into the city’s treasury, but can drive away the citizens not willing to pay as much. Higher taxes also slow down residential building level ups, as there is less money left for improvement after expenses are paid.
EconomyPanel.TAX_AREA_DESCRIPTION[Commer:
Commercial taxes are collected from companies' monthly profits.

Tax rates can be set individually based on the different types of goods sold.

Low taxes increase companies' chances of becoming financially successful. Lower taxes also help commercial buildings level up faster, since more money is left over after upkeep expenses are paid.

Higher taxes bring more money into the city’s treasury, but can also cause companies problems by cutting into their profit margin. Higher taxes also slow down commercial building level ups, as there is less money left for improvement after expenses are paid.
EconomyPanel.TAX_AREA_DESCRIPTION[Indust:
Industrial taxes are collected from companies' monthly profits.

Tax rates can be set individually based on the different types of goods manufactured and sold.

Low taxes increase companies' chances of becoming financially successful. Lower taxes also help industrial buildings level up faster, since more money is left over after upkeep expenses are paid.

Higher taxes bring more money into the city’s treasury, but can also cause companies problems by cutting into their profit margin. Higher taxes also slow down industrial building level ups, as there is less money left for improvement after expenses are paid.
EconomyPanel.TAX_AREA_DESCRIPTION[Office:
Office taxes are collected from companies' monthly profits.

Tax rates can be set individually based on different types of immaterial goods manufactured and sold.

Low taxes increase companies' chances of becoming financially successful. Lower taxes also help office buildings level up faster, since more money is left over after upkeep expenses are paid.

Higher taxes bring more money into the city’s treasury, but can also cause companies problems by cutting into their profit margin. Higher taxes also slow down office building level ups, as there is less money left for improvement after expenses are paid.
EconomyPanel.BUDGET_ITEM_DESCRIPTION[Tax:
Taxes are collected from households and companies.

Residential taxes are based on monthly wages. Company taxes are based on monthly profits.

Low taxes encourage new citizens to move into the city, and increase companies' chances of becoming successful. Low taxes also help buildings level up faster, as more money is left over after the building upkeep expenses are paid. 

High taxes bring in more money for the city, but can drive away citizens, and they cut into companies' profits. High taxes also make building leveling up slower, since there is less cash left after paying for upkeep expenses.
EconomyPanel.BUDGET_ITEM_DESCRIPTION[Fee:
Fees are paid by households and companies in exchange for using various services such as education, healthcare, and utilities.

Households and companies adjust their service usage based on how high the fees are. While lower fees increase well-being in the city, they may not be enough to cover the service’s operating cost entirely. This leaves the city to pay for the rest.
EconomyPanel.BUDGET_ITEM_DESCRIPTION[Exp:
Surplus from city services can be traded with surrounding cities in exchange for additional income.

For example, visitors can use the city’s healthcare services, and vacancies in schools can get filled by students from other cities. Surplus fresh water and sewage treatment capacity as well as excess electricity are automatically sold to surrounding cities as long as the proper utilities connections have been built (pipes for water and sewage, power lines for electricity).
EconomyPanel.BUDGET_ITEM_DESCRIPTION[Gov: The government automatically grants the city subsidies depending on its economic situation. A small city in an overall weak financial situation with poor tax revenue and low service fees receives a fair amount of subsidies, while a larger city in a good financial situation with high revenue stream receives only negligible to no subsidies.
EconomyPanel.BUDGET_ITEM_DESCRIPTION[Sub:
Households and companies will receive city subsidies when their tax rates are set in the negative. This will give them a financial boost and exempt them from paying tax. With subsidies, households have more money to level up their building after paying for expenses. Subsidized companies have higher profit margins, and thus they are also able to spend more money on leveling up their businesses.

Subsidies can be set on the **Taxation** tab, and they are adjustable based on citizen education levels for households and material and immaterial goods manufactured and sold for companies.
EconomyPanel.BUDGET_ITEM_DESCRIPTION[Upk:
Service upkeep costs consist of the service building’s operating costs (building maintenance and resources used to provide its service such as fuel for a power plant) and the wages of its employees.

Service buildings only provide the amount of each service required by the city at any given time, up to their maximum capacity. Accordingly, they only employ the required number of employees at all times. 

To save on operating costs, it is possible to lower the quality of a service on the **Services** tab. This decreases the number of employees hired, but will also lead to poorer performance. For example, waiting times for ambulances will be longer, and police and fire departments will have increased response times due to short-staffing.
EconomyPanel.BUDGET_ITEM_DESCRIPTION[Imp:
Certain services can be imported from surrounding cities. These include education, electricity, water and sewage, police and fire services, road maintenance, healthcare services and garbage services.

Imported services cost the city more than having them provided locally, but importing may be useful when the city is low on space, for example. The overall cost of an imported service is determined by actual usage amounts.
EconomyPanel.BUDGET_ITEM_DESCRIPTION[Loa:
If the city takes a loan, it needs to pay monthly interest based on the loaned amount.

Whenever a new loan is taken, it is combined into any existing loan, and the monthly interest is calculated based on the combined total. Loan interest is a monthly running cost and does not reduce the loaned amount. Loans can be taken and paid back on the **Loans** tab.
EconomyPanel.SERVICE_FEES_REVENUE_DESCRI: Citizens and companies pay fees for using the city's services. The fees offset some of the service upkeep costs.
EconomyPanel.SERVICE_EXPORT_REVENUE_DESC: The city gains income from exporting excess services via Outside Connections.
EconomyPanel.SERVICE_UPKEEP_EXPENSE_DESC: Upkeep consists of building maintenance and resource costs.
EconomyPanel.SERVICE_IMPORT_EXPENSE_DESC: The city can import services from Outside Connections, but importing incurs expenses.
EconomyPanel.BUDGET_ITEM_DESCRIPTION[Til: The monthly cost associated with the maintenance of all the unlocked map tiles.
EconomyPanel.PRODUCTION_DATA_TOOLTIP:
Displays the current flow of the selected resource in your city — where it’s coming from, how it’s processed, and where it’s going.
The chart shows how a resource can have multiple alternative input resources and how a resource itself is split between various refining processes as an input resource. The chart also shows the actual volumes, surpluses, and bottlenecks so you can fine-tune your production chain.
EconomyPanel.PRODUCTION_CHAIN_DIAGRAM_TO:
Shows every possible step in the production chain for the selected resource — from raw extraction, through all potential processing methods, to final products or surplus. This view helps you understand the full range of ways the resource can be used in your city’s economy.
Resources can be obtained by **extracting or processing them locally** or by **importing them** if the city doesn't produce the input resource(s) locally.
Some resources have only one use while others have multiple uses including being used as is, used as an input resource for further processing, and being exported.
EconomyPanel.PRODUCTION_CHAIN_ITEM_TOOLT: Surplus is the excess of production of a resource, the amount left over after what is locally used. Surplus is usually exported from the city.
Deficit is the lack of production of a resource, the amount still needed for local use. Deficit requires importing resources from outside connections to match the current need.
Coal is a natural resource extracted from the ground through mining. Requires an ore deposit.
Inexpensive food sold to customers in retail stores.
Home electronics and appliances are sold to customers in retail stores. Electronics components and parts are used to produce immaterial goods at offices.
Food is sold to customers in retail stores and used as part of the services in restaurants and hotels. Food is also stockpiled in emergency shelters.
Furniture is sold to customers in retail stores and used to furnish office workstations.
Grain is a natural resource extracted from the fertile ground through agriculture.
Sorted mail ready to be delivered to recipients in the city.
Hotels provide lodging service to citizens and tourists.
Restaurants provide meals to patrons.
Metals are used in industrial processes.
Money is used by citizens and companies to buy raw materials and material and immaterial goods.
Outgoing Mail is mail collected from the city, waiting to be transported into a sorting facility or to outside connections.
Paper is sold to customers in retail stores, and supplied to offices.
Petrochemicals are sold to customers in retail stores and used in industrial processes, electricity production and building heating.
Plastics are sold to customers in retail stores and used in industrial processes.
Software is used to create other immaterial goods. Industrial companies and offices use software in their daily operations.
Timber is used in industrial processes and to make improvements to buildings when they level up.
Mail collected from the city that has to be sorted first before it can be delivered to the recipients in the city.
Vegetables are a natural resource extracted from the fertile ground through agriculture.
Vehicles are sold to customers in retail stores.
Wood is a natural resource extracted from forests through forestry.
Cotton is a natural resource extracted from the fertile ground through agriculture.
Beverages are sold to customers in retail stores and used as part of the services in bars.
Chemicals are used in industrial processes and sold to customers in retail stores.
Minerals are used in industrial processes.
Steel is used in industrial processes.
Concrete is used to make improvements to buildings when they level up.
Machinery is used in industrial companies as part of their processes.
Pharmaceuticals are sold to customers in retail stores and used as part of the services in healthcare facilities.
Textiles are sold to customers in retail stores.
Bars provide entertainment to patrons.
Financial services are sold to customers over the internet. Industrial companies and offices also use financial services in their daily operations.
Media products are sold to customers over the internet.
Recreation products are sold to customers in retail stores.
Telecom services are sold to customers over the internet. Industrial companies and offices also use telecom services in their daily operations.
Garbage is gathered from buildings in the city and transported to garbage management facilities or outside connections.
Oil is a natural resource extracted from the ground through mining. Requires an oil deposit.
Metal ore is a natural resource extracted from the ground through mining. Requires an ore deposit.
Stone is a natural resource extracted from the ground through mining. Doesn't require a natural resource deposit.

Fish is a natural resource harvested either from open waters through fishing and fish farming or on land through inland fish farming. Open water fishing and fish farming requires adequate fish population.
Electricity uses Petrochemicals and Coal as fuel in electricity generation.
Fire & Rescue stockpile Food in emergency shelters.
Health & Deathcare use pharmaceuticals as part of their services.
Parks & Recreation uses beverages as part of their services.
If the city has a deficit of a resource or good, it is imported into the city from outside connections. Importing is more expensive to the company than obtaining the resources and goods locally.
If the city has a surplus of a resource or good, it will be exported outside to outside connections. Exporting yields less income to the companies than selling their products locally.
When buildings level up, the occupants order a shipment of resources to perform the improvements on the building.
Agriculture extracts raw materials (grain, vegetables and cotton) from the fertile ground and produces livestock anywhere on the map.
Forestry extracts wood raw material from the forests.
Mining extracts raw materials (stone, coal and metal ore) from the ground. Coal and metal ore require natural resource deposits while stone can be quarried anywhere on the map.
Extraction is the process of obtaining raw materials from the map.
Industry uses input resources to process them into other goods which can be either sold to end users or used in further refining processes.
Processing takes one or more input resources and turns them into new material goods.
Commerce takes an input resource and sells it to the end user.
Retail takes an input resource and turns it into new immaterial goods.
Offices use input resources to process them into immaterial goods which can be either sold to end users over the internet or used in further refining processes.
Service takes an input resources and turns it into new immaterial goods.
End users, including both citizens and tourists, of goods and services, whether material and immaterial.
Livestock is a natural resource collected through agriculture. Doesn't require fertile land.
Buildings use petrochemicals and wood for heating during cold weather.

Editor.TOOLTIP[Game.Prefabs.ZoneProperti:
If set TRUE the Zone Buildings will scale the amount of Residential Properties, based on Lot Size and the Building Level. If set to FALSE then this Zone Type will be LOW DENSITY.
Amount of Apartments is calculated in the following formula:
= (1f + 0.25f * (level - 1)) * buildingPrefab.lotSize * m_ResidentialProperties)

If SCALE RESIDENTIALS is set to TRUE, then this Zone type can be MEDIUM or HIGH DENSITY. Value here determines how many Apartments there are per cell of a building. This is then multiplied with Lot Size to get the total amount of Apartments in the building.
If SCALE RESIDENTIALS is set to FALSE, then this Zone type is LOW DENSITY. Amount of Apartments in the buildings are set by the value defined here. No other factor will be taken into consideration or will affect the amount of Apartments.

Space Multiplier represents the abstraction of amount of floors in a building. If the value on Space Multiplier is high the Apartments will be bigger. Does not affect how many Apartments are in a building. If value of Residential Properties is higher than Space Multiplier, then the zone type will be High Density, otherwise it will be Medium Density.

Editor.TOOLTIP[Game.Prefabs.PollutionPre:
A multiplier value used when calculating how much a building generates ground pollution.
Formula: ((Building pollution value * Pollution type multiplier) / 256) - (Pollution type fade / 256)

A multiplier value used when calculating how much a building generates air pollution.
Formula: ((Building pollution value * Pollution type multiplier) / 256) - (Pollution type fade / 256)

A multiplier value used when calculating how much a building generates noise pollution.
Formula: ((Building pollution value * Pollution type multiplier) / 256) - (Pollution type fade / 256)
A multiplier value used when calculating how much a road segment generates air pollution.
A multiplier value used when calculating how much a road segment generates noise pollution.

The maximum radius an asset spread ground pollution from its origin. 
Note: Ground pollution is not generated equally from the entire building lot, but instead from its origin point, usually in the middle of the building.

The maximum radius an asset spread air pollution from its origin. 
Note: Air pollution is not generated equally from the entire building lot, but instead from its origin point, usually in the middle of the building.

The maximum radius an asset spread noise pollution from its origin. 
Note: Noise pollution is not generated equally from the entire building lot, but instead from its origin point, usually in the middle of the building.
The maximum radius a road segment spreads noise pollution.

The spreading pattern of air pollution. The bigger the value, the wider and far-reaching the "pollution fan" is going to be.
Note: Air pollution spreading is also affected by the strength of the air pollution and Air Fade value.
The rate at which air pollution dissipates after being generated.
The rate at which ground pollution dissipates after being generated.

The rate at which pollution dissipates from trees.
Note: Ground and air pollution decreases the wood resource amount in affected trees.

A multiplier value to calculate wages for commuters from OC.
Example: Commuter working on a Basic level job position earns (Wage 1 x CommuterWageMultiplier)

The city service workers' wage multiplier value.
Note: City service jobs are divided into education levels the same way as other workplaces and pay the same wages as zoned companies' jobs. The wage multiplier adjusts all of the wages.

All company resources added together and compared to the value. If the combined resources value is lower than the limit value, the company goes bankrupt.

Resources include:
- Money resource
- Input (resources the company buys to manufacture other resources)
- Output resources (resources made by the company and stored in the company’s building)
- Resources that are being moved around by vehicles (not yet arrived to other companies or OC)
- Service resources (Entertainment, Lodging, other immaterial resources)

A balancing value deducted from earned wage before taxes are deducted.
Example: (Wage 1 - ResidentialMinimumEarnings) * tax rate = Household tax income
Money paid by the government for citizens who are of working age (teens and adults) but are not working. This allows them to pay Rent and buy resources.
Money paid by the government for senior citizens who don't work anymore. This allows them to pay Rent and buy resources.
Money paid by the government for households per child. This offsets children's resource consumption.

A multiplier value to control how much households consume the resources they have bought and are storing in their household.
X value refers to the poorest households
Y value refers to the wealthiest households.

Note: All resources bought are transformed into a separate monetary resource equal to the value of the resources bought/money spent on the resource acquisition. This “resource money” is separate from the household’s spending money and will be deducted as the household consumes the “resources” aka the resource money.
A resource consumption multiplier value. The value defines the overall daily resource consumption of all citizens in the city.

A resource consumption multiplier value for tourists. The value defines the overall daily resource consumption of all tourists in the city.
Note: Tourists consume resources much in the same way as regular citizens while they are visiting the city.

The schedule when a citizen goes to work.
Note: The 24h day is placed between the values 0 and 1, where 0 means 00.00 (aka start of the day) and 1 means 24:00 (aka the end of the day).
Example: Workday start (0.35) therefore means approximately 7:00 o’clock.

The schedule when a citizen goes back home from work.
Note: The 24h day is placed between the values 0 and 1, where 0 means 00.00 (aka start of the day) and 1 means 24:00 (aka the end of the day).
Example: Workday start (0.35) therefore means approximately 7:00 o’clock.

Global industrial Efficiency balancing value.
Efficiency affects industrial production rate.

Global commercial Efficiency balancing value.
Efficiency affects commercial service rate.

Global specialized industry Efficiency balancing value.
Efficiency affects the extractors’ production rate.

Global value to control how much traffic moves in the city..
Note: Higher value means more vehicles.Lower value means less vehicles and citizens doing their shopping “online”, so that the resources they buy are teleported to their households without them visiting the shops.

The maximum value the City Specialization Bonus can reach in the building’s Efficiency calculation.
City Specialization Bonus affects the zoned buildings’ Efficiency.
City Specialization Bonus resource production coefficient that related to how many production can tend to max bonus [prod/(prod+coefficient) * max].
The percentage value of how much a commercial company contributes to the Rent payments of a mixed housing building.

Multiplier to the Land Value’s effect on different zones’ Rent. The Land Value value within the building’s lot is multiplied by the appropriate modifier.
X: Residential Land Value modifier
Y: Commercial Land Value modifier

ZoneType value in the Rent calculation formula.
Rent formula: (LandValue + (ZoneType * Building Level)) * LotSize * SpaceMultiplier
X: Residential ZoneType
Y: Commercial ZoneType

Controls the Rent curve per building level.
Residential Building's final upkeep is calculated by upkeep multiply with the building level's exponent, higher level has higher upkeep.

Controls the Rent curve per building level.
Industrial Building's final upkeep is calculated by upkeep multiply with the building level's exponent, higher level has higher upkeep.

A balancing value for Office zone demand based on Industrial zone production of resource units.
When the Office zone is unlocked, industrial production starts to affect the Office demand so that a set amount of industrial resources being produced “require” a set amount of Office resources such as Software, Banking etc.
Example: The value of 2000 means that 2000 units of industrial resources produced affects the demand for offices by “requiring” 1 unit of office resources being produced.

The number of days a citizen can receive unemployment benefit.
Once they stop receiving the benefit and haven’t found a new job, they either move out of the city or become homeless.

A balancing value used to divide all of the household’s resources to determine the probability of the household’s next shopping action.

EventJournal.OPENING_MESSAGE:
The **Event Journal** collects every noteworthy event that takes place in the city. 
The list allows you to check back on **what** has been happening, **when** it happened, and what the **effects** were.
Infoviews.INFOMODE_TOOLTIP[Education Cov: Elementary Schools provide a passive well-being bonus in their vicinity to families with children which affects their Happiness. Does not affect children’s ability to attend a school.
Infoviews.INFOMODE_TOOLTIP[Residential B:
Residential buildings are divided into **single-household** and **multi-household** buildings. Detached houses have one household each, while row houses and apartment buildings contain multiple households. 
Single household buildings generate less traffic, but are strongly affected by high **land value**, since the building upkeep cost falls on one family. 
Large apartment buildings generate more traffic and **noise pollution**, but are less affected by high land value, since the building upkeep cost is divided between all the households in the building.
Infoviews.INFOMODE_TOOLTIP[Land Value So: Various buildings increase **Land value** in their vicinity. Land value in turn affects the development of zoned buildings.
Infoviews.INFOMODE_TOOLTIP[Empty Residen: Empty buildings are buildings that either don't have any renters or have been abandoned.
Infoviews.INFOMODE_TOOLTIP[Empty Commerc: Empty buildings are buildings that either don't have any renters or have been abandoned.
Infoviews.INFOMODE_TOOLTIP[Empty Industr: Empty buildings are buildings that either don't have any renters or have been abandoned.
Infoviews.INFOMODE_TOOLTIP[Empty Office: Empty buildings are buildings that either don't have any renters or have been abandoned.
Infoviews.INFOMODE_TOOLTIP[Empty Extract: Empty buildings are buildings that either don't have any renters or have been abandoned.
Infoviews.INFOMODE_TOOLTIP[Homeless]:
Citizens can become **homeless** if they cannot afford rent, move out as adults from their parents’ home without finding a new home, or lose their home due to events or player actions.

Homeless citizens find shelter in the city’s parks, other recreation buildings and abandoned residential buildings. Providing low-cost housing, such as medium-density and low-rent apartment buildings, helps homeless citizens to find new homes.

Intercity **public transportation** gives homeless citizens the option to leave the city if they cannot find new homes.
Infoviews.INFOMODE_TOOLTIP[Destroyed]: An **abandoned** building will eventually **collapse** due to no one paying for the building's upkeep costs. A building can also be **destroyed** by a **building fire**, or a **natural disaster** such as a tornado. When a building becomes damaged enough, it collapses. A collapsed building is destroyed and cannot be repaired. It will be demolished in time by the Fire Station's Disaster Response Unit, or it can be bulldozed manually for immediate removal.
Infoviews.INFOMODE_TOOLTIP[Outside Tradi:
Companies trade with outside connections to optimize their profitability.
When local supply is insufficient to sustain production, companies will **import** resources from outside connections.
If companies produce more resources than the city requires, they will **export** resources to outside connections.

LifePath.OPENING_MESSAGE:
This panel allows you to follow the lives of the citizens of your choosing. You can see what they're doing, where they're going, where they work and live, and who they choose to live with.

To start following a citizen's life path, open their info panel, and press the **Follow** button!
