Loading.HINTMESSAGE:0: Tram tracks can be built directly on top of existing roads. No need to redo anything.
Loading.HINTMESSAGE:1: If you're running out of space to build, see if you can purchase a new Map Tile!
Loading.HINTMESSAGE:2: When placing a City Service building, you're shown the service coverage area of existing buildings of the same type.
Loading.HINTMESSAGE:3: Outside Connections are any land, sea or air routes out of your city. They handle export, import, and tourist traffic.
Loading.HINTMESSAGE:4: Many tools can be used in different modes. Check the bottom left of the screen for options.
Loading.HINTMESSAGE:5: Residential zones work best near workplaces.
Loading.HINTMESSAGE:6: Commercial zones work best near potential customers.
Loading.HINTMESSAGE:7: Industrial zones work best near resources, but also create pollution.
Loading.HINTMESSAGE:8: Existing zones can be re-zoned by simply assigning a new zone type on top of the old one.
Loading.HINTMESSAGE:9: Reaching new Milestones allows access to new City Services.
Loading.HINTMESSAGE:10: By adjusting taxes, you can decide how much residents, companies and industries pay towards the city budget.
Loading.HINTMESSAGE:11: The budget for each City Service can be individually adjusted in the City Economy screen.
Loading.HINTMESSAGE:12: After each work shift, City Service vehicles need to spend some time out of action for refueling, maintenance, and so on. Some upgrades shorten this period.
Loading.HINTMESSAGE:13: In addition to ground level, roads and tracks can also be built on elevated platforms as well as underground.
Loading.HINTMESSAGE:14: Freshwater can be pumped from underground deposits as well as from rivers and lakes.
Loading.HINTMESSAGE:15: Info Views display information about the city with visual overlays. These help you understand what's happening and where.
Loading.HINTMESSAGE:16: Zoned buildings have 5 development levels. Higher level buildings have increased upkeep costs, but also produce less garbage and pollution. They also consume less water and electricity.
Loading.HINTMESSAGE:17: Natural disasters may strike the city at random. Warning systems and emergency shelters can help your citizens when that happens. Natural Disasters can also be disabled from the options menu.
Loading.HINTMESSAGE:18: Natural resources are used by the local industry. When you have active Agriculture, Forestry, Oil Drilling or Mining industries, other related industries also appear.
Loading.HINTMESSAGE:19: Each citizen, vehicle and building can be individually selected. This opens an info panel that shows you more information.
Loading.HINTMESSAGE:20: Advanced forms of City Service buildings can be unlocked in the Milestone panel, under their specific development trees.
Loading.HINTMESSAGE:21: Keep an eye on Chirper, the social media feed. Your citizens are sure to write when things are going well. Or poorly.
Loading.HINTMESSAGE:22: You can pause or speed up the flow of time whenever necessary. The controls are in the bottom left corner of your screen.
Loading.HINTMESSAGE:23: Most City Service buildings can be further upgraded after being built. Upgrades enhance the operating capacity of the building or provide additional functionalities.
Loading.HINTMESSAGE:24: You can enact Policies to change how certain things in the city function. Citywide policies can be activated on the City Info panel, and district policies from the Info Panels of individual districts.
Loading.HINTMESSAGE:25: Weather and traffic cause wear on roads, which leads to lower driving speeds and makes accidents more likely. Road repairs are handled by the Road Maintenance city service.
Loading.HINTMESSAGE:26: Access to Medical, Police, and Firefighting helicopters is granted by building the Helipad upgrade on relevant City Service buildings.
Loading.HINTMESSAGE:27: Most buildings need a road connection, since roads come with integrated electricity and water infrastructure.
Loading.HINTMESSAGE:28: Pay attention to groundwater deposit locations to avoid polluting them when placing industrial zones or fuel burning power plants.
Loading.HINTMESSAGE:29: All in-game guidance texts are collected in the Advisor panel in the top right corner of your screen, so you can return to them whenever necessary.
Loading.HINTMESSAGE:30: Purchasing new Map Tiles requires both money as well as enough Expansion Permits.
Loading.HINTMESSAGE:31: Your Global Theme setting defines the default style of buildings and roads. You can always change this in-game if you wish.
Loading.HINTMESSAGE:32: The parallel mode in tool options allows you to build two sets of roads or tracks next to each other.
Loading.HINTMESSAGE:33: Existing City Service and Signature buildings can be moved to a new location by opening the building info panel and selecting Relocate.
Loading.HINTMESSAGE:34: Electric buses are available through a Bus Depot upgrade.
Loading.HINTMESSAGE:35: If you want a City Service to only work inside a certain district, open the building info panel and select Operating Districts.
Loading.HINTMESSAGE:36: Pay attention when building water pumping stations. Polluted water will make citizens sick.
Loading.HINTMESSAGE:37: The number of turning lanes in an intersection is affected by the road types. Try using asymmetric roads where you need more turning lanes.
Maps.MAP_DESCRIPTION[Delta]: A large, snaking river splitting into a delta is the centerpiece of this map. Surrounded by hills, the terrain is mostly flat, with large contiguous land masses offering plenty of buildable area. The delta, while seemingly tricky to navigate, grants great access to shipping traffic and a natural way to create outside connections.
MapTilePurchase.TITLE: Purchase map tiles
MapTilePurchase.PURCHASE_STATUS[Insuffic: Not enough permits nor enough funds
Maps.MAP_DESCRIPTION[Archipelago]: A chain of islands enveloped by water, this map comprises atolls, lagoons, and peninsulas. A highway running across the map connects some of the larger islands while also providing a connection to the outside world. The buildable area is split over several pieces of land, which offers a range of options for traffic over land, water and air.
Maps.MAP_DESCRIPTION[Mountain Village]: Grassland plains in the midst of a mountain range. Water flowing from the hills creates a river valley in the center of this map with a breathtaking view in every direction. The buildable area between the mountains is fairly flat, but space is at a premium here, so careful planning will be of the essence.
Maps.MAP_DESCRIPTION[Highlands]: Craggy hills and flat-topped mountain ranges dominate this map. Long, narrow lakes split the land in places, while plateaus between the mountains offer suitable locations for city building. The coastline, while dotted by rocky islands, affords traffic by sea.
Maps.MAP_DESCRIPTION[Lakeland]: Beautiful and serene landscape filled with lush forests, sparkling lakes, and rolling hills. Breathtaking views create a delightful backdrop to any city built here, and the low height variation of the terrain ensures there is plenty of space to build. The two existing highways are connected to each other, which allows for plenty of truck traffic into the city early on.
Maps.MAP_DESCRIPTION[Coast]: A small river splitting the map in two runs between flat-topped, steep-sided mountain formations. A gentle slope runs from the mountains to eventually turn into a wide ocean coastline dotted with numerous cliffs and beaches. Without any pre-existing train tracks, a railway connection must be created from scratch.
Maps.MAP_DESCRIPTION[Fjords]: Reaching the coastline requires careful navigation past several long and narrow inlets surrounded by steep cliffs. Luckily, the inland is comfortably flat with plenty of space for expansion, and multiple small rivers offer more than enough options to solve the city's water needs. Highways and train tracks occasionally need tunnels in order to cross the massive cliffs dominating the area.
Maps.MAP_DESCRIPTION[River Valley]: Two colossal mountain ranges create a natural border from two sides, while providing ample flat space for building between them. A large, meandering river flows in the middle of the map joined by a few smaller brooks from the mountains. Train tracks run across the entire area, making it easy to tap into the existing railway network for quick outside access.
Maps.MAP_DESCRIPTION[Plains]: The vast ocean can be accessed from multiple smooth beaches nestled between rising cliffs. Opposite the ocean, a long and tall mountain range creates a marvelous landscape. A broad expanse of flat land provides plenty of buildable space between the ocean and the mountains. A single highway runs through the entire length of the map.
Maps.MAP_DESCRIPTION[Barrier Island]: A long chain of barrier islands has huge potential for prime real estate right from the start. Highway and railway tracks follow the coastline on the mainland, which is separated from the islands by a large bay. An existing shipping lane runs across the bay and connects to the open ocean.
Maps.MAP_DESCRIPTION[San Francisco]: The iconic peninsula characterized by steep hills and sweeping views of the bay. The map is surrounded by water, with the Pacific Ocean to the west and the San Francisco Bay to the east. The Golden Gate Bridge spans the strait, connecting San Francisco to Marin County.
Maps.MAP_DESCRIPTION[Tampere]: Tampere, home of Colossal Order, is known for its stunning natural beauty and waterways. The map is located on an isthmus between two large lakes, Näsijärvi and Pyhäjärvi, which are connected by a river. The surrounding landscape is characterized by lakes, rolling hills and dense forests. Three linked highway connections can easily form the backbone of the city's traffic.
Maps.MAP_DESCRIPTION[Corral Riches]: A vast coastline expanse filled to the brim with natural resources. The center is dominated by a large lake, accompanied by sizable islands suitable for building. Multiple outside connections provide additional opportunities for resource production and transportation of goods.
Maps.MAP_DESCRIPTION[Sunshine Peninsula]: A peninsula comprising a plateau and some islands, basking in the eternal sunshine and the warm sea breeze. The terrain provides a lot of easily buildable space to found a thriving city. With literally no rain and steady warm temperatures throughout the year, this is an ideal choice for those loving the sun.
Maps.MAP_DESCRIPTION[Lakeside Harbour]: A beautiful landscape between two great lakes and ridges rich in natural resources. The lakes are connected with a streaming river which leaves plenty of options for connecting the two sides. The great lakes provide long strides of shoreline where gleaming harbours can be built.
Maps.MAP_DESCRIPTION[Verdant Vale]: A long, wide serpentine river runs across the flat vale. River and the coast are pebbled with small islands where creativity can thrive. The area is lush with resources and has accessible outside connections.
Maps.MAP_DESCRIPTION[Sanctuary Bay]: The large bay with scattered islands form a mesmerizing formation of beaches and peninsulas. Towering cliffs hold the ore and oil while the flat center of land host the large forests and fertile areas. Together these provide an amplitude of riches for the city to grow on. The highways and train tracks create an easy access to the outside world.
Maps.MAP_DESCRIPTION[Driftwood Reach]: The peninsula is connected to the mainland only through a narrow strip of land. The surrounding water has minimal flow, posing challenges for water management. The terrain is relatively flat with only a few elevated places. Some islands dot the coastline and large underwater oil deposits off the coast offer opportunities for industrial interests.
Maps.MAP_DESCRIPTION[Ribbon Isles]: In this vast expanse of stretching islands, nature's bounty thrives. Rich in both ore and oil, Ribbon Isles offer abundant natural resources waiting to be tapped. Dramatic cliffs and small mountains overlook the islands and the narrow waterways challenge even the most seasoned sea captain.

Unity Editor is required to build and post process C# code mods.
Unity license (Personal license is free) is required to use Unity Editor.
Unity Mod Project (UMP) is a minimal Unity project to acquire packages such as Entities and Burst.
.Net is required for various things, tooling and helpers.

Node.js is required for UI modding.

PhotoMode.PROPERTY_TOOLTIP[PhotoModeRend: Defines the distance between the sensor and the camera lens. This determines the vertical field of view. Smaller focal lengths result in a larger field of view, and vice versa.
PhotoMode.ENVIRONMENT_DISCLAIMER: Changing environment properties such as time of day or cloudiness may affect simulation
PhotoMode.PROPERTY_TOOLTIP[PhotoModeRend: Defines the width and height of the sensor that captures the image in millimeters. These affects the aspect ratio.
Offsets the camera's lens from its sensor horizontally and vertically. This allows to change the focal center and reposition a subject in the frame with little to no distortion.
Defines the f-stop (f-number) of the lens. Lower values give a wider lens aperture.
Defines the number of blades in the lens aperture. Higher values give a rounder aperture shape.
Controls the curvature of the lens aperture blades. The minimum value results in fully-curved, perfectly-circular bokeh, and the maximum value results in visible aperture blades.
Controls the self-occlusion of the lens, creating a cat's eye effect.
Stretches the sensor to simulate an anamorphic look. Positive values distort the Camera vertically, negative will distort the Camera horizontally.
Sets the light sensitivity of the Camera sensor.
Defines the amount of time in seconds the camera sensor is capturing light.
Determines how the rendered area (resolution gate) fits into the sensor area (film gate).
Sets the focus mode for the depth of field. Physical or manual.
Sets the distance of the focus plane from the camera. Only used with physical focus mode.
Sets the distance from the camera at which the near field blur begins to decrease in intensity. Only used with manual focus mode.
Sets the distance from the camera at which the near field does not blur anymore. Only used with manual focus mode.
Sets the distance from the camera at which the far field starts blurring. Only used with manual focus mode.
Sets the distance from the Camera at which the far field blur reaches its maximum blur radius. Only used with manual focus mode.
Sets the maximum radius the near blur can reach.
Sets the maximum radius the far blur can reach.
PhotoMode.PROPERTY_TOOLTIP[MotionBlur.in: Sets the intensity of the motion blur effect. Acts as a multiplier for velocities.
PhotoMode.PROPERTY_TOOLTIP[MotionBlur.mi: Controls the minimum velocity, in pixels, that an object must have to contribute to the motion blur effect.
PhotoMode.PROPERTY_TOOLTIP[MotionBlur.ma: Controls the maximum velocity, in pixels, that an object must have to contribute to the motion blur effect.
PhotoMode.PROPERTY_TOOLTIP[MotionBlur.de: Value used for the depth based weighting of samples. Tweak if unwanted leak of background onto foreground or viceversa is detected.
PhotoMode.PROPERTY_TOOLTIP[Bloom.thresho: Set the level of brightness to filter out pixels under this level. This value is expressed in gamma-space. A value above 0 will disregard energy conservation rules.
PhotoMode.PROPERTY_TOOLTIP[Bloom.intensi: Controls the strength of the bloom filter.
PhotoMode.PROPERTY_TOOLTIP[Bloom.scatter: Sets the radius of the bloom effect.
PhotoMode.PROPERTY_TOOLTIP[Vignette.inte: Controls the strength of the vignette effect.
PhotoMode.PROPERTY_TOOLTIP[Vignette.colo: Specifies the color of the vignette.
PhotoMode.PROPERTY_TOOLTIP[Vignette.cent: Sets the center point for the vignette in device coordinates [0-1].
PhotoMode.PROPERTY_TOOLTIP[Vignette.smoo: Controls the smoothness of the vignette borders.
PhotoMode.PROPERTY_TOOLTIP[Vignette.roun: Controls how round the vignette is, lower values result in a more square vignette.
When enabled, the vignette is perfectly round. When disabled, the vignette matches shape with the current aspect ratio.
PhotoMode.PROPERTY_TOOLTIP[FilmGrain.int: Set the strength of the film grain effect.
PhotoMode.PROPERTY_TOOLTIP[FilmGrain.res: Controls the noisiness response curve. The higher this value, the less noise in brighter areas.
PhotoMode.PROPERTY_TOOLTIP[FilmGrain.typ: Specifies the type of grain to use.
PhotoMode.PROPERTY_TOOLTIP[PaniniProject: Controls the panini projection distance. This controls the strength of the distortion.
Controls how much cropping is applied to the screen with the panini projection effect. A value of 1 crops the distortion to the edge of the screen.
PhotoMode.PROPERTY_TOOLTIP[ColorAdjustme: Adjusts the brightness of the image just before color grading, in EV.
Controls the overall range of the tonal values.
Specifies the color of the tint.
Controls the hue of all colors in the render.
Controls the intensity of all colors in the render.
Controls the color temperature HDRP uses for white balancing.
Controls the white balance color to compensate for a green or magenta tint.
PhotoMode.PROPERTY_TOOLTIP[ShadowsMidton: Controls the brightness of the shadows.
Controls the brightness of the midtones.
Controls the brightness of the highlights.
CinematicCamera.UNSAVED_DISCLAIMER: Unsaved changes will be lost. Continue?
CinematicCamera.DELETE_DISCLAIMER: Are you sure you want to delete {NAME}?
PhotoMode.PROPERTY_TOOLTIP[CameraApertur: Collection of properties that controls the physical aperture shape of the camera.
PhotoMode.PROPERTY_TOOLTIP[CameraBody]: Collection of properties that controls the physical body of the camera.
PhotoMode.PROPERTY_TOOLTIP[CameraLens]: Collection of properties that controls the physical lens of the camera.
PhotoMode.PROPERTY_TOOLTIP[DepthOfField]:
Collection of properties that controls the depth of field effect.
Depth of field is used to make near and far objects out of focus look blurry.
PhotoMode.PROPERTY_TOOLTIP[MotionBlur]:
Collection of properties that controls the motion blur effect.
Motion blur is used to mimic streaking of moving objects.
PhotoMode.PROPERTY_TOOLTIP[Bloom]:
Collection of properties that controls the bloom effect.
Bloom is used to mimic fringes of light extending from the borders of bright areas in an image.
PhotoMode.PROPERTY_TOOLTIP[ShadowsMidton: Collection of properties that controls the brightness of Shadows, Midtones and Highlights.
PhotoMode.PROPERTY_TOOLTIP[FilmGrain]:
Collection of properties that controls the film grain effect.
Film grain is used to simulate the noisy look of processed photographic celluloid.
PhotoMode.PROPERTY_TOOLTIP[Vignette]:
Collection of properties that controls the vignette effect.
A vignette is a darker border at the periphery of the frame.
PhotoMode.PROPERTY_TOOLTIP[PaniniProject:
Collection of properties that controls the panini projection.
A panini projection is a cylindrical projection that helps keep vertical straight lines straight and vertical.
PhotoMode.PROPERTY_TOOLTIP[WhiteBalance]: Collection of properties that controls the image white balance.
PhotoMode.PROPERTY_TOOLTIP[ColorAdjustme: Collection of properties that controls the image colors.
PhotoMode.PROPERTY_TOOLTIP[CloudLayer]: Collection of properties that controls the look of distance clouds.
PhotoMode.PROPERTY_TOOLTIP[VolumetricClo: Collection of properties that controls the look of volumetric clouds.
PhotoMode.PROPERTY_TOOLTIP[PhysicallyBas: Collection of properties that controls the look of the sky and atmosphere.
PhotoMode.PROPERTY_TOOLTIP[Fog]: Collection of properties that controls the look of the fog.
PhotoMode.PROPERTY_TOOLTIP[CloudLayer.op: Sets the global opacity of the distance clouds. A value of 0 makes clouds completely transparent.
PhotoMode.PROPERTY_TOOLTIP[CloudLayer.la: Sets the altitude of the distance clouds in meters. This value is used to calculate the sun light attenuation.
Sets a tint to the distance clouds.
Sets the exposure compensation of the clouds in EV relative to the sun light.
Sets the angle in degrees to rotate the distance clouds.
Sets the density of the distance clouds.
Sets the opacity of the cumulus distance cloud layer.
Sets the opacity of the stratus distance cloud layer.
Sets the opacity of the cirrus distance cloud layer.
Sets the opacity of the wispy distance cloud layer.
PhotoMode.PROPERTY_TOOLTIP[VolumetricClo: Controls the global density of the cloud volume.
Controls the larger noise passing through the cloud coverage. A higher value will yield less cloud coverage and smaller clouds.
Controls the size of the larger noise passing through the cloud coverage.
Controls the world space offset applied when evaluating the larger noise passing through the cloud coverage.
Controls the smaller noise on the edge of the clouds. A higher value will erode clouds more significantly.
Controls the size of the smaller noise passing through the cloud coverage.
Controls the type of noise used to generate the smaller noise passing through the cloud coverage.
Controls the altitude of the bottom of the volumetric clouds volume in meters.
Controls the size of the volumetric clouds volume in meters.
Controls the number of steps when evaluating the clouds' transmittance. A higher value results in a lower noise level and longer view distances.
Controls the number of steps when evaluating the clouds' lighting. A higher value will lead to smoother lighting and improved self-shadowing.
Controls the influence of the sun light on the cloud volume. A lower value will suppress the sun light and produce darker clouds overall.
Controls how much erosion factor is taken into account when computing ambient occlusion.
Specifies the tint of the cloud scattering color.
Controls the amount of local scattering in the clouds. A higher value may produce a more powdery or diffused aspect.
Controls the amount of multi-scattering inside the cloud.
Controls the opacity of the volumetric clouds shadow.
PhotoMode.PROPERTY_TOOLTIP[Fog.meanFreeP: Controls the density at the base of the fog and determines how far you can see through the fog in meters. At this distance, the fog has absorbed and out-scattered 63% of background light.
PhotoMode.PROPERTY_TOOLTIP[Fog.baseHeigh: Sets the height of the boundary between the constant (homogeneous) fog and the exponential fog.
PhotoMode.PROPERTY_TOOLTIP[Fog.maximumHe: Controls the rate of falloff for the height fog in meters. Higher values stretch the fog vertically. At this height , the falloff reduces the initial base density by 63%.
PhotoMode.PROPERTY_TOOLTIP[Fog.tint]: Sets a multiplier for the sky color.
PhotoMode.PROPERTY_TOOLTIP[Fog.albedo]: Sets the color of the volumetric fog.
PhotoMode.PROPERTY_TOOLTIP[Fog.depthExte: Controls the distance in meters at which the volumetric fog section of the frustum ends.
PhotoMode.PROPERTY_TOOLTIP[Fog.anisotrop: Controls the angular distribution of scattered light. 0 is isotropic, 1 is forward scattering, and -1 is backward scattering.
PhotoMode.PROPERTY_TOOLTIP[PhysicallyBas: Controls the intensity of aurora borealis.
Sets the depth in meters of the atmospheric layer, from sea level, composed of air particles. This controls the rate of height-based density falloff.
Sets the red color channel opacity of air at the point in the sky directly above the observer (zenith). This directly affects the color of air at the zenith.
Sets the green color channel opacity of air at the point in the sky directly above the observer (zenith). This directly affects the color of air at the zenith.
Sets the blue color channel opacity of air at the point in the sky directly above the observer (zenith). This directly affects the color of air at the zenith.
Controls the single scattering albedo of air molecules (per color channel). A value of 0 results in absorbing molecules, and a value of 1 results in scattering ones.
Sets the depth in meters of the atmospheric layer, from sea level, composed of aerosol particles. This controls the rate of height-based density falloff.
Sets the opacity of aerosols at the point in the sky directly above the observer (zenith). This directly affects the color of aerosols at the zenith.
Controls the single scattering albedo of aerosol molecules (per color channel). A value of 0 results in absorbing molecules, and a value of 1 results in scattering ones.

Specifies the direction of anisotropy:
• Set this value to 1 for forward scattering.
• Set this value to 0 to make the anisotropy almost isotropic.
• Set this value to -1 for backward scattering.
For high values of anisotropy:
• If the light path and view direction are aligned, you see a bright atmosphere/fog effect.
• If they are not aligned, you see a dim atmosphere/fog effect.
• If anisotropy is 0, the atmosphere and fog look similar regardless of view direction.
Controls the saturation of the color of the sky.
Controls the saturation of the opacity of the sky.
Sets a multiplier to the opacity of the sky.
Specifies a color used to tint the sky at the horizon.

Controls how the blends between the horizon tint and zenith tint is performed. For a value of -1, the zenith tint expands down to the horizon. For a value of 1, the horizon tint expands up to the zenith.
Specifies a color used to tint the point in the sky directly above the observer (the zenith).
PhotoMode.PROPERTY_TOOLTIP[VolumetricClo: Controls the world space X component offset applied when evaluating the larger noise passing through the cloud coverage.
Controls the world space Y component offset applied when evaluating the larger noise passing through the cloud coverage.
Controls the world space Z component offset applied when evaluating the larger noise passing through the cloud coverage.

Policy.DESCRIPTION[Out of Service]: The building becomes non-operational. Only maintenance personnel visit the building anymore, so upkeep cost, electricity and water consumption drop to a very low level.
Policy.DESCRIPTION[Lot Parking Fee]: A fee is charged for parking on this lot. The cost of parking can be adjusted with the slider.
Policy.DESCRIPTION[Recreational Use]: Increases the city attractiveness for adult tourists and increases the well-being of the residents in the affected area.
Policy.DESCRIPTION[Fire Safety Sprinkler: Reduces the fire hazard of buildings in the affected area, but increases the level up cost.
Policy.DESCRIPTION[Recycling]: Citizens in the area are encouraged to recycle. This will reduce the amount of used resources but decreases free time.
Policy.DESCRIPTION[Roadside Parking Fee]: A fee is charged for parking on the roadside. The cost of parking can be adjusted with the slider.
Policy.DESCRIPTION[Small Business Enthus: Slightly reduces the tax paid by Low Density Businesses within the district.
Policy.DESCRIPTION[Speed Bumps]: Reduces the speed of vehicles driving within the district. This lowers the chance of accidents and brings noise pollution down significantly.
Policy.DESCRIPTION[Combustion Engine Ban: Fuel burning vehicles are forbidden from entering unless they belong to district residents or businesses. This reduces noise and air pollution within the district.
Policy.DESCRIPTION[Heavy Traffic Ban]: Trucks and other heavy vehicles are forbidden from entering the district. This reduces noise and air pollution and can help traffic congestion. Highways remain unaffected.
Policy.DESCRIPTION[Gated Community]: Only people living or working within the district are allowed in. This increases the well-being of its residents and reduces crime in the area. Does not affect City Services.
Policy.DESCRIPTION[Energy Consumption Aw: Citizens are advised to pay attention to their use of electronic devices. Electricity consumption is reduced by 5%.
Policy.DESCRIPTION[Route Vehicle Count]:
Modify the number of vehicles on the line.
Note that it takes a while for the new vehicles to be prepared in the depot before they are sent out.
Policy.DESCRIPTION[PreRelease Programs]: Prisoners are enrolled in educational programs before they are released from prison. This helps them integrate back into society and reduces the likelihood of committing crimes again.
Policy.DESCRIPTION[City Promotion]: Advertising increases the city's Attractiveness, which brings in more tourists. This unfortunately also increases the crime rate around tourist attractions.
Policy.DESCRIPTION[Advanced Pollution Ma:
Industrial filters reduce air and ground pollution of industrial zone buildings, but they will produce more garbage.
- Air & Ground Pollution -25%
- Garbage Accumulation +15%
Policy.DESCRIPTION[High-Speed Highways]:
Removes highway speed limits so all vehicles can drive their maximum speed. Also increases the probability of traffic accidents.
- Traffic Accident Probability +10%
Policy.DESCRIPTION[Paid Outside Services:
The city imports city services from neighboring cities to either cover a missing city service or to assist the existing city services with more service vehicles. The imported service costs are based on the city's population and multiplied by every 1000 citizens.

Services included: Police, Healthcare, Deathcare, Garbage Management and Fire and Rescue services.
Policy.DESCRIPTION[Taxi Starting Fee]: A base fare is applied to each taxi ride. This is added to the fare based on the actual distance traveled.
Progression.NODE_DESCRIPTION[BasicRoadSe: Basic road services provide the basic infrastructure for building a road network.
Progression.NODE_DESCRIPTION[LargeRoadsN: Very wide, multi-lane roads that allow for high speeds and are good for areas that have a very high traffic demand.
Progression.NODE_DESCRIPTION[Roundabouts: Roundabouts are a handy alternative to regular intersections, and allow for traffic to flow more smoothly.
Progression.NODE_DESCRIPTION[ParkingArea: Cars need parking spaces, and areas of high activity can benefit from dedicated parking areas.
Progression.NODE_DESCRIPTION[HighwaysNod: These high-speed, high-capacity roads connect distant locations to each other and cities to outside connections. The high road speeds generate noise pollution and do not allow zoning around highways.
Progression.NODE_DESCRIPTION[AutomatedPa: An automated parking garage that uses elevators to lift and stack vehicles in small slots on top of each other. This saves plenty of street level space.
Progression.NODE_DESCRIPTION[GrandBridge: A magnificent bridge that will be a landmark of the city.
Progression.NODE_DESCRIPTION[BasicElectr: Basic energy production facilities and network infrastructure.
Progression.NODE_DESCRIPTION[GasPowerPla: Gas-fired power plants provide the city with cost-effective large-scale energy solutions with moderate pollution emissions.
Progression.NODE_DESCRIPTION[WaveEnergyC: Wave energy converters use the movement of waves to generate electricity.
Progression.NODE_DESCRIPTION[NuclearPowe: Nuclear power plants produce massive amounts of energy with minimal emissions. Their maintenance, however, is expensive and requires well-educated workers.
Progression.NODE_DESCRIPTION[BasicWater&: Basic water and sewage services provide the city with the facilities and infrastructure for delivering freshwater and processing sewage.
Progression.NODE_DESCRIPTION[WaterReserv: Water reserve tanks are facilities that provide water supply during water shortages and peak use times.
Progression.NODE_DESCRIPTION[WaterTreatm: Water treatment is the processing and purification of wastewater. Treated water can be safely recirculated into the water network or disposed of in the environment.
Progression.NODE_DESCRIPTION[Crematorium: Crematoriums cremate the bodies of deceased citizens.
Progression.NODE_DESCRIPTION[HospitalNod: Hospitals provide both basic healthcare as well as specialized treatment, which help citizens remain healthier.
Progression.NODE_DESCRIPTION[DiseaseCont: The study of pathogens, toxins, and hereditary diseases and ways to treat them helps citizens recover from even the most serious of conditions.
Progression.NODE_DESCRIPTION[HealthResea: The Health Research Institute studies ways of keeping citizens healthier and educates them in various ways via, for example, lectures and outdoor challenges.
Progression.NODE_DESCRIPTION[BasicGarbag: Basic garbage management provides the city with a landfill site that sends out garbage trucks to collect garbage from households, companies and services.
Progression.NODE_DESCRIPTION[RecyclingCe: The recycling center collects and sorts garbage to produce reusable materials. Selling the recycled materials creates additional income for the city.
Progression.NODE_DESCRIPTION[IndustrialW: The industrial waste processing facility collects and handles toxic waste products resulting from industrial production. As a result, the ground pollution produced by industrial buildings is lowered.
Progression.NODE_DESCRIPTION[BasicFire&R: Basic fire & rescue services provide the city with fire houses and fire engines, which are essential in various firefighting and rescue operations.
Progression.NODE_DESCRIPTION[FirewatchTo: These towers keep a constant lookout and thus reduce the chance of a forest fire.
Progression.NODE_DESCRIPTION[FireStation: Fire stations are larger fire houses that are better prepared in firefighting and rescue operations, and can cover a larger service area.
Progression.NODE_DESCRIPTION[EmergencySh: Emergency shelters provide citizens a safe place to stay during large-scale accidents or natural disasters.
Progression.NODE_DESCRIPTION[EarlyDisast: The EDWS contains multitudes of high-end detection systems that can spot approaching natural disasters in advance, reducing their impact on the city.
Progression.NODE_DESCRIPTION[LargeEmerge: This massive shelter can house a significant number of citizens for an extended period of time during even the most dangerous disasters.
Progression.NODE_DESCRIPTION[BasicPolice: Basic police & administration services provide the city with police stations and patrol cars.
Progression.NODE_DESCRIPTION[PoliceHeadq: These large station houses have extended administrative and staff facilities, a jail and a large garage for patrol cars, so they can cover a larger service area.
Progression.NODE_DESCRIPTION[PrisonNode]: Prisons are used to hold convicted criminals.
Progression.NODE_DESCRIPTION[CentralInte: The Central Intelligence Bureau investigates severe criminal activity and apprehends criminals with superior efficiency. The sole existence of this office lowers the crime rate citywide.
Progression.NODE_DESCRIPTION[BasicEducat: Basic education services provide the most basic and necessary education to children and teenagers.
Progression.NODE_DESCRIPTION[CollegeNode: The college provides the first step towards higher education for teens and adults alike.
Progression.NODE_DESCRIPTION[UniversityN: The university provides adults with the highest level of education.
Progression.NODE_DESCRIPTION[GeologicalR: A facility for performing geological research and field studies. Helps discover larger underground deposits of ore and oil.
Progression.NODE_DESCRIPTION[BasicTransp: Basic transportation services provide the city with the most basic forms of public transport.
Progression.NODE_DESCRIPTION[HarborNode]: The harbor services provide the city with both passenger and cargo ship facilities.
Progression.NODE_DESCRIPTION[TrainNode]: Trains allow for a large number of passengers or large amounts of cargo to be transported over tracks.
Progression.NODE_DESCRIPTION[TramNode]: Trams are rail vehicles that carry passengers inside the city.
Progression.NODE_DESCRIPTION[SubwayNode]: Subways are underground trains that can transport a large number of passengers with ease.
Progression.NODE_DESCRIPTION[AirportNode: The airport allows airplanes to operate from the city.
Progression.NODE_DESCRIPTION[Internation: The international airport handles international air traffic. Has integrated taxi and train connections for the ease of travel. The airport makes the city more attractive for tourists and makes offices and commercial companies more effective.
Progression.NODE_DESCRIPTION[SpaceCenter: The ChirpX Space Center is both a space museum as well as an active command center and rocket launch platform. These attract tourists and increase the effectiveness of industries and offices.
Progression.NODE_DESCRIPTION[BasicParks&: The parks & recreation services provide the city with parks and other recreational facilities.
Progression.NODE_DESCRIPTION[LargeParksN: Large parks and plazas provide enjoyment for a larger area and can accommodate a greater number of visitors.
Progression.NODE_DESCRIPTION[SportsParks: Sports parks include various recreational facilities.
Progression.NODE_DESCRIPTION[ParkMainten: Park maintenance services keep all parks, plazas and other recreational facilities clean and in good condition.
Progression.NODE_DESCRIPTION[LargeSports: Large sports parks include facilities suitable for team sports and other sports that require more space.
Progression.NODE_DESCRIPTION[HistoricalA: Historical attractions are buildings and sites with historical importance.
Progression.NODE_DESCRIPTION[TouristAttr: Tourist attractions provide entertaining and cultural attractions for tourists.
Progression.NODE_DESCRIPTION[AmusementPa: Amusement parks include theme parks, zoos and other recreational attractions for citizens and tourists.
Progression.NODE_DESCRIPTION[BasicCommun: Basic post services for collecting and delivering mail in the city.
Progression.NODE_DESCRIPTION[PostSorting: The post sorting facility processes and stores mail for dispatch. Mail is collected from post offices and mailboxes and delivered to post offices and outside connections.
Progression.NODE_DESCRIPTION[RadioMastsN: Radio masts provide the city with enhanced coverage for mobile devices, radio and television.
Progression.NODE_DESCRIPTION[ServerFarmN: A server farm is a collection of computer servers maintained by the city and they are used to supply the city with more network capacity.
Progression.NODE_DESCRIPTION[TelecomTowe: The telecom tower provides a wide range of telecommunications services ranging from intercontinental television broadcasts to long range cellular networks, greatly increasing network capacity city-wide.
Progression.NODE_DESCRIPTION[SatelliteUp: The satellite uplink is a large dish that can broadcast and receive data, television and radio signals from across the globe. A satellite uplink facility increases both the network capacity and entertainment city-wide as well as the entertainment values of certain buildings.

Progression.NODE_DESCRIPTION[BasicHealth: Basic healthcare services provide citizens with medical clinics and ambulances for medical treatment and emergencies, as well as deathcare services such as cemeteries for those who have passed away.
Progression.NODE_DESCRIPTION[AdvancedRoa: Road maintenance facilities, traffic lights and signs as well as roadside decorations.
Progression.NODE_DESCRIPTION[AdvancedEle: The station reduces the negative effects buildings suffer from when there is no electricity. Produces a low amount of noise pollution.
Progression.NODE_DESCRIPTION[SolarPowerS:
Photovoltaic cells generate electricity from sunlight. It is stored in batteries during daytime and fed into the network during nights. As power is generated from sunlight alone, power output depends on the weather, but the plant also does not produce any ground or air pollution.
Can be upgraded with a backup battery, an advanced tracking system, and high voltage substations.
Progression.NODE_DESCRIPTION[GeothermalP: Geothermal power plants convert underground heat into electricity while generating only some air and noise pollution.
Progression.NODE_DESCRIPTION[WelfareOffi: The welfare office provides financial support for low-income citizens, which increases their well-being and lowers the likelihood of recurring crime.
Progression.NODE_DESCRIPTION[Incinerator: The incinerator plant burns garbage and produces electricity from the heat. The burning produces high amounts of ground pollution as well as some air and noise pollution.
Progression.NODE_DESCRIPTION[RadioTelesc: This astronomical research facility creates more interest in university studies and increases the likelihood of university students graduating.
Progression.NODE_DESCRIPTION[LargeCoalPo: A large, more powerful coal-burning power production facility. Generates high amounts of air, ground and noise pollution like its smaller counterpart.
Progression.NODE_DESCRIPTION[Hydroelectr: Hydroelectric power plants convert the energy of flowing water into electricity. Produces some noise pollution in the process.
Progression.NODE_DESCRIPTION[LargeHadron: A very large and powerful particle collider that is used for physics experimentation. Increases interest in university studies and creates higher demand for electronics and software companies.
Progression.NODE_DESCRIPTION[Underground: An underground parking garage that saves space on the street level, freeing it to be utilized in other ways.
Progression.NODE_DESCRIPTION[Intersectio: Ready-made, large intersections that allow highways to be seamlessly connected to the city's regular road network.
Progression.NODE_DESCRIPTION[HeliportNod: The depot provides the city with more firefighting helicopters that can be used by the Fire & Rescue service to quickly respond to fire emergencies.
Progression.NODE_DESCRIPTION[Desalinatio: A highly efficient and powerful surface water pumping station.
Progression.NODE_DESCRIPTION[TechnicalUn: The technical university provides academic learning for the technically oriented. Increases the efficiency of offices and industrial companies.
Progression.NODE_DESCRIPTION[MedicalUniv: The medical university provides academic schooling for medical professions. Increases the efficiency of healthcare service buildings.
Progression.MILESTONE_VICTORY_DESCRIPTIO: You’ve Made it. You have succesfully built your city!

You’ve Made it. You have succesfully built your city!
Your dedication and skill as a mayor have led you to this remarkable achievement. You can choose to continue playing to further explore and enjoy your city building journey. Please note that the game may become less stable beyond this point. We recommend saving your progress frequently if you decide to continue.

Thank you for playing and making it as a mayor!
Progression.MILESTONE_VICTORY_CONFIRM_NE: Do you want to save your current game before you start building a new city?
Progression.NODE_DESCRIPTION[CityHallNod:
The city hall is a center for different branches of local government. A more efficient bureaucracy decreases the upkeep of city service buildings and reduces the price of imported city services.
Unlocks the City Promotion city policy.
Progression.NODE_DESCRIPTION[CentralBank: The central bank houses stock and resource traders as well as financial advisors and loan officers. It decreases the loan interest rate and and improves citizens' happiness tax effect tolerance

Radio.EMERGENCY_MESSAGE[Tornado Radio Ev: A tornado is passing through, causing severe damage to buildings. Affected citizens are seeking emergency shelter.

SelectedInfoPanel.CITIZEN_CONDITION_DESC: The citizen is unable to work, and may die if their condition doesn't improve.
The citizen is unable to work, and needs time to recover from their injuries.
The citizen has no permanent residence in the city, and will leave if they can't find a new home.
The citizen's well-being is extremely low.
The citizen's health is extremely low.
The citizen is affected by a natural disaster. Their health and well-being decrease as long as they remain in the disaster area.
The citizen is in an emergency shelter. Their well-being decreases as long as they remain there, but will recover soon after they are able to leave the shelter.
SelectedInfoPanel.CITIZEN_HAPPINESS_DESC:
The citizen is depressed. They are not well and their **health** has declined greatly.

The citizen requires basic utilities like fresh water and electricity where they live, possibilities for **leisure** activities to increase their **well-being** and basic healthcare to increase their **health**.

The citizen is sad. Their **well-being** and **health** have declined. Citizens with low **well-being** are more inclined to turn into criminals. Low **health** increases their chances of getting **sick** and lowers their ability to work.

The citizen requires basic utilities like fresh water and electricity where they live, possibilities for **leisure** activities to increase their **well-being** and basic healthcare to increase their **health**.

The citizen is calm and neutral. They have their basic needs mostly covered and they are neither happy or sad.

In order to be a more productive member of the society, their **well-being** and **health** can be improved by offering them **leisure** possibilities and better healthcare options. Making sure that they don't live in areas of high pollution is also important part of increasing their **happiness**.

The citizen is content. They are relatively happy and satisfied with their life and the place where they live in. They are productive members of the society and contribute somewhat to their workplace's success, as well. Improving their **well-being** and **health** will improve their work efficiency.

The citizen is happy. Their life is fulfilling, they are able to live and work where they desire and they enjoy their free time to the fullest. Services and activities are available and nearby, and the citizen contributes greatly to their workplace's success.

SelectedInfoPanel.DESTROYED_DESCRIPTION[: This building has been destroyed by a lightning strike.

This building was abandoned and has collapsed due to lack of maintenance.
Fire Station's Disaster Response Unit is required to search for survivors in the collapsed building and to clear out the rubble afterwards. If the city can't provide the response units, they can be imported from Outside Connections.
SelectedInfoPanel.TOOLTIP[ActionsSection: Toggle the visibility of traffic routes and associated paths connected to the selected object.
SelectedInfoPanel.TOOLTIP[ResidentsSecti: The number of homeless people sheltering in this building.
SelectedInfoPanel.TOOLTIP[ExtractorVehic: Specialized industry vehicles extract and transport resources from the area to the hub building, where they are then shipped to end users.
SelectedInfoPanel.TRADED_RESOURCES_TOOLT: Traded resources include all resources that can pass through and be stored at this facility.
SelectedInfoPanel.TOOLTIP[CargoTransport:
Cargo transport vehicles are owned by transport depots, and transport **goods** or **resources** between stations along predefined cargo routes.

They operate continuously on the route to ensure they are readily available whenever cargo needs to be transported. The number of vehicles operating on the route can be adjusted in the Route info panel.

Selecting the **owner**, **destination**, or **route** opens their individual info panels.
SelectedInfoPanel.TOOLTIP[PublicTranspor:
Public transport vehicles travel on predetermined **lines** and transport **citizens** and **tourists** around the city. Citizens use them to commute, go shopping or to travel to leisure activities.

They operate continuously on the line to ensure they are readily available whenever passengers need to be transported. The number of vehicles operating on the line can be adjusted in the Line info panel.

Selecting the **owner**, **destination**, or **line** opens their individual info panels.
SelectedInfoPanel.TOOLTIP[StorageSection: Companies store both the input resource(s) used in manufacturing and the output resource before it is sold to another company or the end user.

If there is enough of the resource in storage, it is marked as **Balanced**. If the resource is marked as **Surplus**, it is likely to be shipped to local companies that use it, other warehouses, or exported to Outside Connections. If the resource is marked as **Deficit**, it is likely to be imported from other warehouses, from companies that produce it, or from Outside Connections.

If there is enough of a resource in storage, it is marked as **Balanced**. If a resource is marked as **Surplus**, it is likely to be exported. If a resources is marked as **Deficit**, it is likely to be imported into the city.
SelectedInfoPanel.TOOLTIP[LevelSection]: Money that is left over after paying **rent** and **upkeep** is used by the occupants to **level up** the building. When the building is about to level up, the occupants order a shipment of concrete and timber to perform the improvements on the building. If the occupants' **wealth** declines, the building may end up **abandoned**.
SelectedInfoPanel.SELECT_VEHICLE_MULTIUN: These carriage models cannot be used with separate engine models.
SelectedInfoPanel.TOOLTIP[StorageSection: Service buildings store resources required for their basic operations.
SelectedInfoPanel.TOOLTIP[LineSectionWor:
Length is the distance from the start of the route to the finish.

Stops is the current number of stops along the length of the route.
Services.DESCRIPTION[Communications]: Post offices, mail delivery, mobile networks and wireless broadband all fall under the Communications services.
Services.DESCRIPTION[Districts]: City Districts are defined areas inside the city that can have specific policies, architectural styles and city services assigned to them.
Services.DESCRIPTION[Education & Researc: Schools, colleges and universities that provide education and prepare citizens for different jobs, and research facilities that make progress easier.
Services.DESCRIPTION[Electricity]: Electricity can be produced in various ways and distributed throughout the city with different means.
Services.DESCRIPTION[Fire & Rescue]: Fires, accidents and natural disasters are all handled by the Fire & Rescue services.
Services.DESCRIPTION[Garbage Management]: Waste produced by the citizens is collected, stored and processed by the Garbage Management service.
Services.DESCRIPTION[Health & Deathcare]: Healthcare services keep citizens healthier by preventing disease and by treating the sick and injured. Deathcare services handle citizens who have passed on.
Services.DESCRIPTION[Landscaping]: The ground can be shaped and formed, vegetation and decorations added and pedestrian traffic options built with Landscaping tools.
Services.DESCRIPTION[Parks & Recreation]: Recreational areas and facilities make the city a more pleasant place to live in.
Services.DESCRIPTION[Police & Administra: The Police enforce the law and apprehend criminals, while Administration handles the courts, banking and welfare.
Services.DESCRIPTION[Transportation]: Moving passengers and cargo by land, sea or air are all covered by the Transportation services.
Services.DESCRIPTION[Water & Sewage]: Buildings and pipes to pump and deliver fresh water to the city and remove sewage.
Services.DESCRIPTION[Zones]: Zoning determines what kinds of buildings are allowed to be built and where. Zones can be assigned next to roads, and they are divided into different types.
Services.DESCRIPTION[Signatures]: Signature buildings are special unique buildings that grant XP awards and provide various benefits to their surroundings.
Services.DESCRIPTION[Areas]: Tools to define Districts and Specialized Industry areas.
UpgradesMenu.TITLE: Upgrades
Services.DESCRIPTION[Roads]: Roads are the main city infrastructure. Most of them come with underground utility networks that handle electricity, water and sewage.
Assets.SUB_SERVICE_DESCRIPTION[CulDeSacs: Transforms road ends into zoneable cul-de-sacs, with the zoneable area determined by the road size and the selected cul-de-sac type.
Assets.SUB_SERVICE_DESCRIPTION[Transport: Ferries use the city's waterways to transport citizens and tourists within the city. It's a good alternative to ground-based public transport methods.
Assets.SUB_SERVICE_DESCRIPTION[PiersAndQ: Piers and quays designed for pedestrian access and to enhance the city's aesthetic appeal.
